WEBVTT

00:50.180 --> 00:53.357
[WOMAN] IT WAS A NAME
THAT SOUNDED SO SWEET,

00:53.401 --> 00:54.271
SO SEDUCTIVE.

00:57.144 --> 00:59.059
SYNONYMOUS WITH WEALTH...

01:00.495 --> 01:01.800
STYLE...

01:03.324 --> 01:04.368
POWER.

01:05.848 --> 01:08.807
YOU PASSED ONE OF THEIR WINDOWS
AND PEEKED INSIDE,

01:08.851 --> 01:11.245
HOPING YOU'D EARN ENOUGH
MONEY SOMEDAY

01:11.288 --> 01:13.943
TO AFFORD
THE SECOND-CHEAPEST ITEM.

01:17.990 --> 01:19.209
SURPRISE!

01:21.168 --> 01:22.386
YOU WON'T.

01:28.262 --> 01:30.786
BUT THE LAST NAME
WAS A CURSE TOO.

01:35.443 --> 01:37.532
IT BELONGED TO A TUSCAN FAMILY.

01:41.188 --> 01:45.670
THEY DIDN'T FIGHT
OVER LAND OR CROWN.

01:48.804 --> 01:50.327
-MORNING!
-[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

01:50.371 --> 01:51.763
[WOMAN] THEY FOUGHT OVER
THEIR OWN SKINS.

01:52.895 --> 01:53.983
[MAN] SIGNORGUCCI?

01:55.898 --> 01:58.030
["LA RAGAZZA COL MAGLIONE"
PLAYING]

02:34.241 --> 02:36.634
[MAN 1 WOLF-WHISTLES]

02:36.678 --> 02:38.288
[MAN 2 SHOUTING IN ITALIAN]

02:38.332 --> 02:39.985
[MAN 3 LAUGHS]

02:40.029 --> 02:41.596
[MAN 4 SHOUTING IN ITALIAN]

02:43.032 --> 02:44.773
[MEN SHOUTING IN ITALIAN]

02:45.252 --> 02:46.035
[MAN LAUGHS]

02:49.473 --> 02:50.779
HEY! BACK TO WORK.
COME ON.

02:50.822 --> 02:51.823
HEY! COME ON.

02:52.607 --> 02:53.390
[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

02:54.826 --> 02:56.393
[MAN 1 SPEAKS ITALIAN]

02:56.437 --> 02:58.047
[MAN 2 WOLF-WHISTLES]

03:01.485 --> 03:03.357
[MAN 3 SPEAKING ITALIAN]

03:03.400 --> 03:04.662
-[MAN 4 WOLF-WHISTLES]
-[MAN 5 SPEAKING ITALIAN]

03:06.577 --> 03:07.491
[DOG BARKING]

03:33.865 --> 03:35.171
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

03:42.700 --> 03:44.789
[MAN] PERFECT!
IT'S JUST LIKE MINE.

03:44.833 --> 03:46.748
FERNANDO REGGIANI.

03:46.791 --> 03:48.619
[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

03:48.663 --> 03:49.881
GOOD GIRL.

03:49.925 --> 03:51.796
-HEY, FERNANDO.
-HEY.

03:51.840 --> 03:54.364
YOUR LUNCHES ARE GETTING
EXPENSIVE.

03:54.408 --> 03:56.148
BECAUSE I HAVE
EXPENSIVE TASTE, HUH?

03:56.845 --> 03:57.933
[CHUCKLES]

03:59.543 --> 04:00.979
DON'T TELL MA.

04:01.023 --> 04:02.633
SHE'LL KILL YOU.

04:02.677 --> 04:04.679
-[TELEPHONE RINGING]
-YOU DON'T TELL YOUR MOTHER.

04:04.722 --> 04:06.115
[CHUCKLES]

04:07.203 --> 04:08.117
HELLO.

04:08.900 --> 04:11.120
MAX! DARLING.

04:12.513 --> 04:13.557
TONIGHT?

04:16.430 --> 04:17.996
I THINK I'M FREE.

04:18.040 --> 04:18.823
[DISCO MUSIC PLAYING]

04:24.264 --> 04:26.178
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

04:36.841 --> 04:38.408
DO YOU LIKE IT? YEAH?

04:39.714 --> 04:40.932
THIS IS FUN!

04:45.763 --> 04:47.722
[PEOPLE CHEERING]

04:50.420 --> 04:51.943
NO, NO.

05:09.309 --> 05:12.790
TANQUERAY MARTINI
WITH A TWIST.

05:12.834 --> 05:15.053
I DON'T WORK HERE.

05:15.097 --> 05:16.794
THEN WHY ARE YOU
BEHIND THE BAR?

05:16.838 --> 05:17.926
[MAN CHUCKLES]

05:17.969 --> 05:19.667
IS THIS PART OF YOUR COSTUME?

05:20.276 --> 05:21.190
I, UH...

05:22.409 --> 05:24.454
I DIDN'T KNOW IT WAS
A COSTUME PARTY.

05:25.542 --> 05:27.022
THE...

05:27.065 --> 05:28.676
THE BARTENDER... [MUTTERS]

05:30.286 --> 05:31.896
YEAH, I...

05:31.940 --> 05:33.071
I'LL MAKE YOU A DRINK.

05:34.334 --> 05:35.857
THANK YOU.

05:39.687 --> 05:41.297
WHO INVITED YOU?

05:41.341 --> 05:42.864
BIANCA.

05:42.907 --> 05:44.256
I DON'T KNOW HER.

05:45.257 --> 05:46.563
BIANCA SARZANA.

05:49.740 --> 05:50.698
IT'S HER PARTY.

05:52.482 --> 05:53.570
OH. [LAUGHS]

05:53.614 --> 05:56.573
RIGHT. THAT BIANCA. [CHUCKLES]

05:58.488 --> 05:59.663
I'M PATRIZIA.

06:00.751 --> 06:01.839
PATRIZIA...

06:04.320 --> 06:05.365
MAURIZIO GUCCI.

06:06.670 --> 06:08.280
IT'S A PLEASURE TO MEET YOU,
PATRIZIA.

06:10.500 --> 06:11.458
IT'S A PLEASURE TO MEET YOU!

06:12.676 --> 06:13.851
YOU TOO.

06:15.157 --> 06:18.029
PATRIZIA, HOW COME I'VE NEVER
SEEN YOU BEFORE?

06:19.770 --> 06:22.251
YOU WEREN'T LOOKING
HARD ENOUGH.

06:22.294 --> 06:23.687
I WOULD HAVE NOTICED
THAT BIANCA

06:23.731 --> 06:26.037
WAS FRIENDS
WITH ELIZABETH TAYLOR.

06:26.081 --> 06:27.256
I CAN ASSURE YOU...

06:29.084 --> 06:30.520
I'M WAY MORE FUN.

06:36.047 --> 06:37.179
IT'S GOOD.

06:41.139 --> 06:42.271
WANNA DANCE?

06:43.272 --> 06:44.273
NO.

06:47.798 --> 06:49.104
THAT'S GOOD. COME ON.

07:08.732 --> 07:10.517
[SOULFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

07:27.534 --> 07:28.970
IS MY DANCING THAT BAD?

07:29.013 --> 07:30.319
NO, NO, NO. NO.

07:33.365 --> 07:34.758
I HAVE TO GO.

07:34.802 --> 07:37.587
IT'S ONLY MIDNIGHT, CINDERELLA.

07:37.631 --> 07:39.371
THE NIGHT IS YOUNG.

07:39.415 --> 07:41.678
I TURN INTO A FROG AT MIDNIGHT.

07:50.208 --> 07:51.558
IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU,
PATRIZIA.

08:00.567 --> 08:02.090
IT'S A PUMPKIN.

08:02.133 --> 08:03.395
NOT A FROG.

08:42.391 --> 08:43.784
HELLO.

08:43.827 --> 08:44.567
HELLO.

08:47.222 --> 08:48.789
I'M SORRY, HAVE WE MET?

08:57.058 --> 08:58.059
ELIZABETH TAYLOR.

09:00.061 --> 09:02.759
-PATRIZIA REGGIANI.
-YES, OF COURSE.
PATRIZIA REGGIANI.

09:06.894 --> 09:08.460
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

09:08.504 --> 09:09.461
YOU TOO.

09:09.505 --> 09:10.767
DO YOU STUDY HERE?

09:11.681 --> 09:13.422
I'M CONSIDERING IT.

09:13.465 --> 09:17.121
THE PROBLEM IS I HATE READING.
I GET BORED.

09:17.687 --> 09:18.470
OH.

09:21.648 --> 09:22.997
WHAT ARE THOSE ABOUT?

09:23.040 --> 09:24.302
THESE ARE...

09:26.304 --> 09:30.047
WELL, THESE ARE
VERY EXCITING BOOKS

09:30.091 --> 09:32.702
ABOUT THE LEGISLATIVE PROCESS.

09:32.746 --> 09:34.399
I'M STUDYING TO BE A LAWYER.

09:35.618 --> 09:37.359
YOU SEEM TOO NICE
TO BE A LAWYER.

09:37.402 --> 09:41.145
[CHUCKLES] WELL, THERE ARE
A FEW GOOD ONES.

09:41.189 --> 09:43.147
-THE DEAD ONES.
-[LAUGHS]

09:45.585 --> 09:47.325
[ENGINE TURNS OVER]

09:54.985 --> 09:57.901
WHAT WERE THE CHANCES OF US
SEEING EACH OTHER AGAIN?

09:57.945 --> 09:59.294
IT'S FATE.

09:59.337 --> 10:00.469
IT WAS A REALLY NICE SURPRISE.

10:07.607 --> 10:08.390
[CHUCKLES]

10:10.740 --> 10:12.350
AREN'T YOU GOING
TO ASK ME OUT?

10:14.918 --> 10:17.834
YOU... YOU WANNA
GO ON A DATE WITH ME?

10:21.359 --> 10:22.665
OF COURSE, I WOULD...

10:22.709 --> 10:24.536
I WANT TO SEE
HOW THIS STORY GOES.

10:28.149 --> 10:29.280
YES...

10:33.110 --> 10:33.894
[CHUCKLES]

10:35.373 --> 10:36.505
THAT'S MY NUMBER.

10:37.898 --> 10:41.162
I'M VERY BUSY,
BUT I'LL MAKE TIME FOR YOU...

10:42.816 --> 10:44.426
MAURIZIO.

10:49.170 --> 10:50.519
-CIAO.
-CIAO.

10:57.134 --> 10:58.222
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

10:58.266 --> 10:59.441
[MUSIC PLAYING ON HEADPHONES]

11:02.357 --> 11:03.750
IT'S FOR YOU.

11:15.631 --> 11:16.545
HELLO?

11:18.112 --> 11:19.417
[SIGHS]

11:21.855 --> 11:23.813
SO DO YOU THINK YOU'RE GONNA
PASS THE BAR SOON?

11:24.858 --> 11:26.729
I THINK I HAVE A...

11:26.773 --> 11:28.949
WOULD YOU LIKE TO
GO INTO THIS PLACE?

11:28.992 --> 11:31.560
OH, NO. I CAN'T EAT THERE.
IT'S TOO EXPENSIVE.

11:32.604 --> 11:33.562
OKAY.

11:35.651 --> 11:37.348
OKAY, I CAN TRY.

11:37.392 --> 11:38.567
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GO IN?

11:40.569 --> 11:43.572
[PATRIZIA CHUCKLES]

11:49.099 --> 11:50.448
NO? OKAY.

11:50.492 --> 11:51.275
AH!

11:52.581 --> 11:53.625
THIS IS FOR YOU.

11:54.844 --> 11:57.455
IT LOOKS SO GOOD.
THANK YOU.

11:57.499 --> 11:59.370
THAT'S ALL RIGHT.
CAN I HAVE A NAPKIN?

12:00.458 --> 12:01.677
CAN I HAVE A BITE?

12:05.115 --> 12:07.074
MMM. SO GOOD. HERE.

12:07.509 --> 12:08.292
MM.

12:17.867 --> 12:19.390
[PATRIZIA CHUCKLES]

12:19.434 --> 12:20.870
OH, THAT'S VERY GOOD.

12:33.317 --> 12:34.623
COME ON.

12:45.939 --> 12:46.896
OKAY.

12:53.294 --> 12:54.425
[PATRIZIA LAUGHING]

13:03.652 --> 13:04.871
-[PATRIZIA] SIT.
-OH, NO.

13:08.352 --> 13:10.224
GET UP.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
ARE YOU OKAY?

13:10.267 --> 13:11.007
[MAURIZIO] I FELL BACK.

13:14.054 --> 13:14.837
OH...

13:15.925 --> 13:16.708
IT'S FINE.

13:32.420 --> 13:33.290
[PATRIZIA CHUCKLES]

14:30.652 --> 14:33.568
FATHER, I WOULD LIKE
TO INTRODUCE YOU
TO PATRIZIA REGGIANI.

14:33.611 --> 14:35.396
PATRIZIA,
THIS IS MY FATHER,
RODOLFO.

14:35.439 --> 14:37.528
DELIGHTED TO MEET YOU.

14:39.052 --> 14:42.490
I TRUST ADELE
HAS BEEN KEEPING
YOU AMUSED.

14:42.533 --> 14:43.839
PICASSO?

14:44.927 --> 14:47.408
NO. NO, NO. NO, IT'S KLIMT.

14:50.454 --> 14:51.020
HOW SILLY OF ME.

14:51.629 --> 14:53.588
OH, NO, NO, NO.

14:53.631 --> 14:56.460
IT'S AN EASY MISTAKE.
I'VE MADE WORSE MYSELF.

14:56.504 --> 14:58.419
MUST BE WORTH A FORTUNE.

14:59.289 --> 15:00.725
[ALL LAUGHING]

15:01.117 --> 15:02.771
YES.

15:02.814 --> 15:07.645
BUT YOU KNOW, TO ME, ART,
LIKE BEAUTY, HAS NO PRICE.

15:07.689 --> 15:09.560
I MADE A RESERVATION FOR US
AT THE GALLIA.

15:09.604 --> 15:10.779
PERFECT CHOICE.

15:11.998 --> 15:13.173
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

15:17.873 --> 15:18.787
[RODOLFO] SO PATRIZIA...

15:19.353 --> 15:20.136
WHAT...

15:21.703 --> 15:23.357
WHAT EXACTLY
ARE YOUR INTERESTS?

15:24.662 --> 15:27.056
I'M A VERY SOCIAL PERSON.

15:27.100 --> 15:28.188
ARE YOU?

15:28.231 --> 15:29.580
-A PEOPLE PLEASER.
-OH.

15:32.844 --> 15:35.804
AND, DO YOU STUDY?

15:37.893 --> 15:40.156
I WORK FOR
MY FATHER'S BUSINESS.

15:40.200 --> 15:41.462
[RODOLFO] AH.

15:41.505 --> 15:43.246
AND HIS BUSINESS IS?

15:47.555 --> 15:48.817
GROUND TRANSPORTATION.

15:54.518 --> 15:55.302
OH.

16:03.527 --> 16:06.835
MAURIZIO SAID
YOU USED TO BE AN ACTOR.

16:07.923 --> 16:09.925
YES, I WAS.

16:09.969 --> 16:13.407
YOU MAY REMEMBER A FILM,
THE ANCESTOR?

16:16.671 --> 16:18.455
NO, NO, NO. OF COURSE.

16:18.499 --> 16:19.848
YOU'RE TOO YOUNG.

16:19.891 --> 16:21.850
BUT SOMETIMES ON THE TV,

16:21.893 --> 16:24.070
THEY PLAY A MOVIE
TOURIST TRAIN.

16:24.113 --> 16:26.289
-TOURIST TRAINSOUNDS FAMILIAR.
-YEAH, WELL...

16:26.333 --> 16:30.859
MAYBE YOU NOTICED
A DASHING YOUNG ACTOR,
MAURIZIO D'ANCORA.

16:32.730 --> 16:34.080
THAT WOULD HAVE BEEN ME.

16:35.472 --> 16:38.345
I DIDN'T KNOW I WAS SITTING
WITH A MOVIE STAR.

16:38.388 --> 16:39.694
CAN I GET AN AUTOGRAPH?

16:39.737 --> 16:41.348
[RODOLFO] OH, NO, NO, NO.

16:41.391 --> 16:44.655
THE ONLY GOOD THING THAT CAME
FROM MY CAREER WAS

16:44.699 --> 16:46.701
MEETING MAURIZIO'S MOTHER.

16:46.744 --> 16:50.357
NOW SHE,
SHE WAS A STAR.

16:52.750 --> 16:54.274
I REMEMBER AT HER FUNERAL...

16:56.102 --> 17:01.324
DURING A MOMENT OF
SILENT REMEMBRANCE,

17:01.368 --> 17:04.501
MAURIZIO NOTICED THE PRIEST
LIGHTING CANDLES...

17:06.373 --> 17:09.811
AND HE BEGAN TO SING
"HAPPY BIRTHDAY."

17:11.421 --> 17:15.904
HE TURNED, MAYBE
THE SADDEST MOMENT OF MY LIFE,

17:17.123 --> 17:18.994
INTO SOMETHING...

17:19.038 --> 17:20.909
HOW DO YOU SAY,
SOMETHING SWEET.

17:24.347 --> 17:25.609
THAT'S MY SON.

17:27.611 --> 17:28.917
THAT IS MY DEAR BOY.

17:52.636 --> 17:54.943
-GRAZIE, FRANCO.
-THANK YOU, SIR.

18:17.183 --> 18:18.967
AH, MAURIZIO.

18:20.055 --> 18:21.970
I LIKED YOUR PATRIZIA.

18:22.753 --> 18:24.015
CHARMING.

18:24.059 --> 18:25.843
FATHER, SHE REALLY
LIKED YOU.

18:31.066 --> 18:32.763
TELL ME,
WHERE DID YOU MEET HER?

18:33.460 --> 18:34.983
I MET HER AT A PARTY.

18:35.766 --> 18:37.507
[RODOLFO] PARTY?

18:37.551 --> 18:40.162
YEAH, LUCA SARZANA'S HOUSE.
AT THE PALAZZO SERBELLONI.

18:40.206 --> 18:41.990
[RODOLFO] YES, I KNOW
WHERE THE SARZANAS LIVE.

18:46.212 --> 18:47.169
YOU KNOW...

18:49.432 --> 18:51.869
THERE IS A CERTAIN SORT OF
YOUNG WOMAN...

18:53.088 --> 18:57.571
WHO MAKES THEIR FORTUNE

18:57.614 --> 19:01.096
FROM GETTING THEIR HOOKS
INTO SOMEONE LIKE YOU.

19:01.140 --> 19:04.230
WELL, YES, FATHER,
BUT PATRIZIA IS NOT LIKE THAT.

19:04.273 --> 19:08.669
[RODOLFO] WELL, I HAD FRANCO
DO A LITTLE INVESTIGATION.

19:08.712 --> 19:10.671
I THINK
SHE'S AFTER YOUR MONEY.

19:10.714 --> 19:12.368
LIKE THEY ALL ARE.

19:12.412 --> 19:13.891
THE REGGIANIS...

19:15.415 --> 19:17.286
ARE TRUCK DRIVERS.

19:17.330 --> 19:19.723
HER FATHER HAS
A VERY SUCCESSFUL

19:19.767 --> 19:21.290
TRANSPORTATION BUSINESS.

19:21.334 --> 19:22.509
IT IS...

19:24.250 --> 19:25.468
IT IS AN EMPIRE.

19:26.861 --> 19:30.081
OH! A TRUCK DRIVING EMPIRE.
HOW MANY?

19:30.125 --> 19:32.432
-HOW MANY WHAT?
-HOW MANY TRUCKS?

19:32.475 --> 19:34.260
FIFTY? FIVE HUNDRED?

19:34.303 --> 19:36.349
WHAT DOES HE TRANSPORT,
GARBAGE? HUH?

19:36.392 --> 19:37.654
MAFIA!

19:38.264 --> 19:39.308
[COUGHING]

19:44.487 --> 19:45.314
OH...

19:47.621 --> 19:49.884
LISTEN, I'VE...

19:50.841 --> 19:52.278
I GIVE YOU EVERYTHING.

19:52.321 --> 19:53.844
I GIVE YOU THIS HOUSE,
I GIVE YOU MONEY.

19:53.888 --> 19:55.498
YOU HAVE A LIFE. YOU...

19:56.673 --> 19:58.240
WHAT IS IT YOU WANT?

20:00.068 --> 20:01.896
WHAT I WANT IS TO MARRY HER.

20:03.376 --> 20:04.942
LIVE WITH HER. FUCK HER.

20:04.986 --> 20:06.509
HAVE A GOOD TIME WITH HER.
DO WHAT YOU WANT.

20:06.553 --> 20:08.250
GO AWAY ON HOLIDAY.
GO TO SARDINIA.

20:08.294 --> 20:09.991
BUT, NO, NOT MARRY.

20:13.864 --> 20:15.736
NO, DON'T WALK AWAY.

20:15.779 --> 20:17.259
OKAY, LISTEN TO YOURSELF.

20:17.303 --> 20:19.261
YOU'RE SO BITTER
AND YOU DON'T EVEN REALIZE IT.

20:19.305 --> 20:21.089
WHO CARES
WHAT HER FAMILY NAME IS,

20:21.132 --> 20:22.786
OR HOW MANY TRUCKS
THEY HAVE.

20:23.874 --> 20:25.746
YOU HIDE HERE IN THE PAST

20:26.877 --> 20:28.749
AND YOU EXPECT ME
TO HIDE HERE WITH YOU?

20:29.706 --> 20:31.317
NOT ANYMORE!

20:33.232 --> 20:34.798
THESE ARE YOUR GHOSTS.

20:37.061 --> 20:38.889
THESE ARE YOUR GHOSTS,
NOT MINE.

20:38.933 --> 20:40.151
THESE ARE YOUR REGRETS.

20:41.240 --> 20:42.458
DON'T DO THIS TO ME.

20:43.720 --> 20:45.766
YOU CAN'T STOP IT.

20:45.809 --> 20:48.159
I CAN, I WILL. I WILL...
I CUT YOU FROM MY WILL.

20:48.203 --> 20:49.378
I'LL LEAVE YOU WITH NOTHING.

20:50.597 --> 20:51.728
THAT'S FINE.

20:53.600 --> 20:55.297
I LOVE HER.

20:55.341 --> 20:57.125
[RODOLFO]
YOU'RE MAKING A BIG MISTAKE.

20:58.387 --> 21:00.998
OH, SHE'S FINE,
BUT, YOU KNOW,

21:01.042 --> 21:03.914
SHE'S A...
SHE'S JUST A...

21:03.958 --> 21:05.176
I LOVE WHAT SHE IS.

21:06.743 --> 21:07.918
[DOORBELL RINGS]

21:22.759 --> 21:24.457
SI?

21:24.500 --> 21:27.024
COMMENDATOREREGGIANI,
MY NAME IS MAURIZIO GUCCI.

21:28.243 --> 21:31.159
-[WOMAN] PATRIZIA!
-[PATRIZIA] UH-HUH?

21:31.202 --> 21:32.595
[WOMAN SPEAKS
IN OTHER LANUGAGE]

21:32.639 --> 21:37.383
I HAVE HAD A DISAGREEMENT
WITH MY FATHER

21:37.426 --> 21:40.255
THAT HAS FORCED ME
TO LEAVE MY HOME
AND MY FAMILY BUSINESS.

21:40.951 --> 21:43.389
I AM STILL IN SCHOOL.

21:43.432 --> 21:46.392
I'M STUDYING TO BE A LAWYER,
SO AS OF THIS MOMENT

21:47.436 --> 21:50.221
I DO NOT HAVE A JOB, BUT I...

21:50.265 --> 21:51.397
[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

21:53.660 --> 21:55.314
BUT I'M IN LOVE
WITH YOUR DAUGHTER.

21:58.578 --> 22:00.362
AND I WOULD LIKE TO MARRY HER.

22:00.406 --> 22:02.321
ALTHOUGH,
NOW I HAVE NOTHING
TO OFFER HER.

22:03.452 --> 22:05.672
I, UH...
I NEED A JOB.

22:09.458 --> 22:10.416
MOM.

22:16.204 --> 22:17.466
MAMA.

22:20.469 --> 22:22.253
["SONO BUGIARDA" PLAYING]

22:43.710 --> 22:44.275
[CHUCKLES]

22:52.458 --> 22:53.633
[LAUGHING]

22:58.377 --> 23:00.335
[ALL CHEERING]

23:11.477 --> 23:13.348
[OVER P.A.] MAURIZIO GUCCI,

23:13.392 --> 23:15.524
YOU'RE URGENTLY NEEDED
IN ACCOUNTING.

23:16.830 --> 23:18.658
[MAN] MAURIZIO!

23:18.701 --> 23:19.920
MAURIZIO!
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

23:41.028 --> 23:42.290
[PATRIZIA]
THAT WAS GREAT.

23:43.596 --> 23:45.641
THE DOOR! THE DOOR!

23:47.904 --> 23:49.776
[PATRIZIA LAUGHS]

24:01.440 --> 24:02.353
PAPA?

24:07.141 --> 24:08.316
PAPA?

24:17.020 --> 24:19.327
[OPERATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

24:23.592 --> 24:26.116
[MEN SHOUTING IN DISTANCE]

24:56.016 --> 24:57.757
[OPERATIC MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

24:59.454 --> 25:01.369
[MOANING]

25:25.088 --> 25:26.525
[MOANING CONTINUES]

25:42.715 --> 25:44.499
[MOANING IN PLEASURE]

25:58.121 --> 25:59.993
[PIPE ORGAN MUSIC PLAYING]

26:03.562 --> 26:04.693
HI, PAPA.

26:17.445 --> 26:18.881
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

26:29.892 --> 26:31.459
CIAO, BELLA, CIAO.

26:40.076 --> 26:42.078
["FAITH" PLAYING]

26:53.307 --> 26:55.091
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

27:22.162 --> 27:23.424
MAURIZIO...

27:25.644 --> 27:27.515
[SAYING VOWS IN ITALIAN]

27:34.740 --> 27:35.741
[REPLIES IN ITALIAN]

27:36.655 --> 27:38.526
[PRIEST SPEAKING ITALIAN]

27:47.448 --> 27:49.450
[CROWD CHEERING, APPLAUDING]

28:08.338 --> 28:10.471
[REPORTERS CLAMORING]

28:37.411 --> 28:38.717
[MAN] WHAT IS THIS?

28:42.372 --> 28:44.157
WHERE IS THIS?

28:44.200 --> 28:44.810
WHAT IS THIS?

28:50.729 --> 28:52.600
WHAT IS THIS?

28:54.167 --> 28:55.603
HOW ABOUT THAT.

29:07.397 --> 29:08.398
[MAN] YES.

29:09.486 --> 29:12.315
-AH, CLAUDIA.
-GOOD MORNING!

29:12.359 --> 29:14.665
-GOOD MORNING, MR. ALDO.
-GOOD MORNING.

29:14.709 --> 29:15.797
-THIS WAY?
-THAT WAY.

29:21.455 --> 29:23.718
KONICHIWA, MR. GUCCI.

29:25.502 --> 29:26.895
[SPEAKS JAPANESE]

29:26.939 --> 29:28.636
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

29:28.679 --> 29:32.248
[RODOLFO] WHAT'S ALL THIS
JAPANESE BULLSHIT?

29:32.292 --> 29:34.120
I'M LEARNING.

29:34.163 --> 29:36.252
YOU KNOW, THEY'RE OUR BEST
CUSTOMERS, SO.

29:37.558 --> 29:40.126
THEY'RE LOYAL,
THEY'RE QUIET.

29:40.169 --> 29:41.475
AND THEY'RE RICH.

29:42.868 --> 29:45.305
ONE OF YOUR TERRIBLE IDEAS.

29:45.348 --> 29:46.828
HERE IT IS.

29:46.872 --> 29:48.830
GOTEMBA.

29:48.874 --> 29:50.571
GOTEMBA?

29:50.614 --> 29:53.008
YEAH, NEAR THE FOOT
OF MOUNT FUJI.

29:53.052 --> 29:54.401
IT'S A MALL.

29:54.444 --> 29:56.707
NINETY MINUTES BY BUS
FROM TOKYO.

29:57.708 --> 29:59.449
IT WILL BE BUILT IN THE SPRING.

30:00.711 --> 30:03.062
A WINDOW
INTO THE ASIAN MARKET.

30:03.105 --> 30:04.454
-NO, NO, NO.
-IT'S A STEPPING STONE.

30:04.498 --> 30:05.804
-NO, NO, NO.
-COME ON!

30:05.847 --> 30:07.893
NO, ALDO.
YOU AND YOUR PROFITS.

30:07.936 --> 30:09.938
COME ON, THINGS ARE FINE
AS THEY ARE.

30:09.982 --> 30:13.855
GUCCI DOESN'T BELONG
IN A MALL,
IT BELONGS IN A MUSEUM.

30:13.899 --> 30:17.250
MUSEUM WHERE
IT'LL MAKE NO PROFIT.

30:17.293 --> 30:19.078
WHAT'S THIS?

30:19.121 --> 30:20.644
NO.

30:20.688 --> 30:24.344
ALDO, AS LONG AS
WE ARE FIFTY-FIFTY,

30:24.387 --> 30:25.519
THAT'S HOW IT STAYS.

30:25.562 --> 30:26.694
NO MALLS.

30:29.436 --> 30:31.394
I SEE MAURIZIO GOT MARRIED.

30:31.438 --> 30:32.439
[RODOLFO] OH, GOD!

30:32.482 --> 30:34.789
SOME... OH, SHE'S...

30:34.833 --> 30:36.051
I CAN'T EVEN SAY HER NAME.

30:37.574 --> 30:39.272
WELL, SOONER OR LATER
YOU WILL HAVE TO.

30:39.315 --> 30:40.708
-NO, NO, NO.
-YES.

30:40.751 --> 30:42.536
NO, MAURIZIO AND I HISTORY.
HISTORY.

30:42.579 --> 30:44.146
-NO, COME ON.
-I DON'T...

30:44.190 --> 30:45.974
YOU ARE OLD.

30:46.018 --> 30:50.718
MAURIZIO IS YOUR ONLY SON.
HE IS YOUR TRUE LEGACY.

30:50.761 --> 30:53.199
-YOU DON'T BRING HIM
BACK INTO THE FOLD...
-WELL, MAYBE...

30:53.242 --> 30:55.201
I'M TELLING YOU...

30:55.244 --> 30:58.508
YOU'LL ONLY WIND UP BEING
A BITTER AND LONELY OLD MAN.

30:58.552 --> 31:00.293
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS
TO ALL OF US.

31:00.336 --> 31:01.990
TIME WILL TELL. BUT...

31:02.034 --> 31:04.732
YEAH. WHEN DID YOU
LAST TOUCH HIM, HUH?

31:04.775 --> 31:06.386
WHEN DID YOU LAST HUG HIM?

31:06.429 --> 31:08.344
YOU DON'T TOUCH ANYBODY.

31:09.868 --> 31:11.739
YOU USED TO TOUCH
EVERY ONCE IN A WHILE,

31:11.782 --> 31:13.915
NOW YOU, WHAT,
TOUCH YOURSELF?

31:13.959 --> 31:16.352
-YOU? YOU, TEACHING ME?
-THAT'S CORRECT.

31:16.396 --> 31:19.616
[STUTTERING] HOW'S IT GOING
WITH YOUR BOY? HMM?

31:19.660 --> 31:23.098
WELL, YOUR SON IS
A SMART LAWYER.

31:23.142 --> 31:24.404
MINE IS AN IDIOT.

31:24.447 --> 31:26.841
BUT HE'S MY IDIOT.

31:26.885 --> 31:28.582
AND I KNOW
HOW TO DEAL WITH HIM.

31:28.625 --> 31:31.454
BUT YOU NEED TO DEAL
WITH YOUR SON.

31:31.498 --> 31:32.760
-AH...
-YES.

31:33.761 --> 31:35.589
IT'S MY BIRTHDAY ON SUNDAY.

31:35.632 --> 31:37.112
YEAH?

31:37.156 --> 31:38.113
WE'LL ALL BE THERE.

31:39.027 --> 31:40.333
YOU SHOULD COME.

31:44.728 --> 31:46.121
I'LL HAVE TO LOOK AT MY DIARY.

31:47.644 --> 31:49.777
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

31:54.608 --> 31:56.175
-HELLO.
-[ALDO] HELLO.

31:56.218 --> 31:57.698
WHO IS THIS?

31:57.741 --> 32:01.963
-SI, THIS IS ALDO. ALDO GUCCI.
-ALDO.

32:02.007 --> 32:04.270
I HOPE I'M NOT INTERRUPTING
ANYTHING IMPORTANT.

32:04.313 --> 32:05.619
WHAT COULD BE MORE IMPORTANT

32:05.662 --> 32:07.490
THAN A PHONE CALL
FROM MY NEW UNCLE?

32:07.534 --> 32:13.192
I AM TRULY SORRY
FOR NOT BEING ABLE TO COME
TO YOUR WEDDING.

32:13.235 --> 32:14.976
IT WAS... I COULDN'T HELP IT.

32:15.020 --> 32:16.064
BUSINESS BECKONED.

32:18.371 --> 32:19.763
EASY ON THAT.

32:21.069 --> 32:23.158
I UNDERSTAND, OF COURSE.
I KNOW HOW BUSY YOU ARE.

32:23.202 --> 32:26.422
WE ARE CELEBRATING MY
BIRTHDAY THIS WEEKEND

32:26.466 --> 32:27.989
AT MY VILLA.

32:28.033 --> 32:29.860
AND I THINK IT WOULD BE

32:29.904 --> 32:33.473
A PERFECT OPPORTUNITY FOR YOU
TO COME AND MEET THE FAMILY.

32:33.516 --> 32:34.822
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

32:34.865 --> 32:36.171
YOUR BIRTHDAY,
I WOULD LOVE THAT.

32:36.215 --> 32:37.694
HOW MANY CANDLES IS IT?

32:37.738 --> 32:39.958
SEVENTY.

32:40.001 --> 32:43.309
THEY SAY IT'S THE NEW
SIXTY-NINE.

32:43.352 --> 32:46.007
WELL, I CAN'T SPEAK
FOR MAURIZIO.

32:46.051 --> 32:47.313
HE'S RIGHT HERE.

32:49.619 --> 32:50.620
[WHISPERS] NO.

32:50.664 --> 32:51.621
PLEASE.

32:58.628 --> 32:59.716
CIAO, ALDO.

32:59.760 --> 33:00.935
MAURIZIO!

33:00.979 --> 33:03.503
HOW IS MY LITTLE LAWYER?

33:03.546 --> 33:05.853
I'M FINE. I'M FINE.

33:05.896 --> 33:07.507
WHAT ARE YOU DOING THIS SUNDAY?

33:09.074 --> 33:10.727
I'LL DOUBLE CHECK.

33:10.771 --> 33:12.947
COME TO MY BIRTHDAY PARTY.

33:12.991 --> 33:14.905
I'M ONLY IN TOWN
FOR A COUPLE OF WEEKS.

33:14.949 --> 33:15.863
COME ON.

33:17.996 --> 33:19.475
LET ME DISCUSS IT
WITH PATRIZIA.

33:19.519 --> 33:21.738
-LET'S GO! A LITTLE DAY TRIP.
-I DON'T...

33:21.782 --> 33:25.046
YOU KNOW, YOUR FATHER AND I
AREN'T GETTING ANY YOUNGER.

33:25.090 --> 33:27.788
THESE GATHERINGS ARE BECOMING
MORE AND MORE

33:27.831 --> 33:30.269
OF A RARE OCCURRENCE,
YOU KNOW.

33:31.139 --> 33:32.358
PLEASE.

33:34.795 --> 33:35.926
COME ON!

33:35.970 --> 33:37.841
I'LL BE JUMPING OUT OF A CAKE.

33:37.885 --> 33:39.887
[OPERATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

33:53.596 --> 33:54.902
[MEN GRUNTING]

34:01.909 --> 34:04.129
COME ON.
KICK HIS TEETH OUT.

34:04.172 --> 34:07.175
COME ON! COME ON!

34:07.219 --> 34:09.612
EARN YOUR FUCKING LUNCH!

34:10.831 --> 34:12.920
KICK HIS TEETH OUT. COME ON!

34:14.139 --> 34:15.749
GO, GO, GO!

34:15.792 --> 34:18.317
THAT'S IT. GO!

34:18.360 --> 34:21.755
MAURIZIO! COME ON!
WE'RE MISSING A PLAYER.

34:21.798 --> 34:24.192
-OH. NO, NO, NO.
-WHAT NO? YES, YES. COME ON.

34:24.236 --> 34:27.108
WE'RE MISSING A PLAYER.
COME ON!

34:27.152 --> 34:29.154
-PUT IT ON.
TAKE THAT JACKET OFF.
-OKAY.

34:29.197 --> 34:30.329
YOU KNOW IT.

34:30.372 --> 34:31.504
PAOLO!

34:31.547 --> 34:32.983
WATCH HIM. WATCH HIM PLAY.

34:33.810 --> 34:35.334
SEE THAT?

34:35.377 --> 34:38.163
OH, MY GOD. LOOK AT THAT.

34:38.206 --> 34:39.903
[MAN] MAURIZIO! MAURIZIO!

34:40.382 --> 34:41.253
[SHOUTS]

34:42.254 --> 34:43.342
[ALDO] THAT'S YOUR HUSBAND!

34:53.221 --> 34:53.961
[GROANS]

34:55.310 --> 34:56.311
PAOLO!

34:58.052 --> 34:59.967
PAPA...

35:00.010 --> 35:04.014
-OH, NO.

35:07.627 --> 35:09.019
HOW DO YOU ACT SHY?

35:12.066 --> 35:13.937
-PAPA!
-"PAPA." I LOVE THAT.

35:15.635 --> 35:18.246
HE'S NEVER IN HIS LIFE
CALLED ME PAPA.

35:18.290 --> 35:20.640
PATRIZIA, YOU SHOULD KNOW...

35:21.597 --> 35:23.599
THAT THE GUCCIS

35:23.643 --> 35:27.647
WERE NOBLE SADDLE-MAKERS
TO MEDIEVAL COURTS.

35:27.690 --> 35:32.565
WE HAVE HISTORY
FLOWING THROUGH THESE
GREEN AND RED WEBBINGS.

35:32.608 --> 35:35.785
AND YES, WE ARE EXPENSIVE.

35:35.829 --> 35:40.355
BUT QUALITY IS REMEMBERED
LONG AFTER PRICE IS FORGOTTEN.

35:41.313 --> 35:43.184
HUH?

35:43.228 --> 35:45.665
THOUGHTS ON PAOLO'S OUTFIT,
DOMENICO?

35:45.708 --> 35:47.014
YOU'RE THE FASHIONISTA.

35:47.667 --> 35:50.365
IT'S ECCENTRIC.

35:51.236 --> 35:53.847
I DESIGNED THIS MYSELF.

35:53.890 --> 35:59.331
WELL, YOU SHOULD RECONSIDER
YOUR WARDROBE CHOICES, PAOLO.

35:59.374 --> 36:02.464
YOU ARE GUCCI,
YOU NEED TO DRESS THE PART.

36:02.508 --> 36:04.031
IT'S CHIC.

36:05.424 --> 36:09.297
MY FATHER'S PROBLEM IS THAT
HE'S STUCK IN THE PAST.

36:09.341 --> 36:13.475
HE REFUSES TO TAKE GUCCI
INTO THE NEXT CENTURY.

36:13.519 --> 36:16.174
-[ALDO] YES, GUCCI IS DOING
FINE UNDER MY WATCH.
-[PAOLO] NO!

36:16.217 --> 36:17.610
-NO, DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
-OH, NO!

36:17.653 --> 36:19.873
NO. NO.

36:19.916 --> 36:21.701
IT NEEDS NEW IDEAS.

36:21.744 --> 36:23.442
-NEW ENERGY.
-OF COURSE.

36:23.485 --> 36:26.314
AND I HAPPEN TO BE
BURSTING WITH CREATIVITY.

36:26.358 --> 36:29.056
-YES, YES.
-YES, MY BLADDER MAY BE FULL...

36:29.926 --> 36:33.147
BUT MY DREAMS ARE EVEN FULLER.

36:33.191 --> 36:35.932
I'M LIKE A RUSH OF WATER.

36:36.716 --> 36:39.501
SOMEBODY BUILD A DAM.

36:39.545 --> 36:41.242
PLEASE.

36:41.286 --> 36:43.940
[PAOLO] YOU'RE ALWAYS
BRUSHING ME OFF.

36:43.984 --> 36:48.336
I'M A DESIGNER.
I NEED TO EXPRESS MYSELF.

36:48.380 --> 36:52.166
-BUT WHY ALL
THIS SUDDEN MOANING?
-I HAVE A...

36:52.210 --> 36:56.649
-[ALDO] WHAT DO YOU WANT?
-[PAOLO] BECAUSE, I'M SO SICK
OF YOU IGNORING ME.

36:56.692 --> 36:58.128
I AM SICK OF YOUR TALKING.

36:58.868 --> 37:00.566
SICK OF IT.

37:00.609 --> 37:03.003
YOU DELIBERATELY HURT
MY FEELINGS.

37:03.046 --> 37:04.918
-[ALDO] YES.
-NO, NO, NO.

37:04.961 --> 37:07.137
-JENNY! JENNY HONEY.
-NO! THAT'S WHAT HE WANTS.

37:07.181 --> 37:09.488
-DON'T. SIT DOWN.
SIT DOWN! SIT DOWN.
-[ALDO] YOU HAVE SUCCEEDED.

37:09.531 --> 37:11.185
I HAVEN'T HAD ESPRESSO.

37:11.229 --> 37:13.274
-[ALDO] BYE.
-THANKS FOR HAVING US, UNCLE.

37:13.318 --> 37:18.061
AH! MY NEPHEW,
HE HAS SUCH GREAT TASTE.

37:18.932 --> 37:21.891
OH. A SMALL WEDDING GIFT.

37:23.980 --> 37:25.373
THANK YOU.

37:25.417 --> 37:28.898
COME TO NEW YORK. OKAY?

37:30.335 --> 37:31.858
-CIAO, ALDO.
-CIAO!

37:31.901 --> 37:33.468
-CIAO.
-[LAUGHS]

37:33.512 --> 37:34.948
[BIDDING FAREWELL IN ITALIAN]

37:34.991 --> 37:36.515
OH, IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU.

37:36.558 --> 37:39.518
I COULDN'T BELIEVE
YOU GOT INTO THE CAR.

37:39.561 --> 37:40.736
HOW DID YOU DO THAT?

37:43.173 --> 37:44.697
[MAURIZIO] IT'S ALL BULLSHIT.

37:44.740 --> 37:45.785
WE'RE NOT ROYALTY.

37:47.265 --> 37:50.006
MY GRANDFATHER GUCCIO WAS
A BELLHOP IN LONDON.

37:50.050 --> 37:53.488
THAT'S WHERE HE GOT THE IDEA
FOR LEATHER GOODS.

37:53.532 --> 37:56.404
BY CARRYING BAGS AROUND
FOR RICH ARISTOCRATS.

37:56.448 --> 37:57.797
GUCCI IS LIKE THAT CAKE.

37:57.840 --> 37:59.929
WHAT?

37:59.973 --> 38:02.758
ONCE YOU THINK THERE'S ENOUGH
TO GO AROUND...

38:04.369 --> 38:07.154
THEN YOU'LL HAVE A TASTE,
AND THEN YOU'LL WANT MORE...

38:07.197 --> 38:09.156
AND THEN YOU'LL WANT
THE WHOLE THING FOR YOURSELF.

38:11.680 --> 38:12.855
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

38:14.683 --> 38:17.120
YOU JUST GONNA SIT AROUND
AND WATCH THEM EAT EVERYTHING?

38:17.860 --> 38:19.732
ME? I AM GUCCI BY NAME.

38:20.994 --> 38:24.432
I DON'T HAVE
THEIR TUSCAN CHARACTER.

38:24.476 --> 38:27.174
IT WAS DILUTED BY
MY MOTHER'S GERMAN BLOOD.

38:34.355 --> 38:37.010
THE ONLY WEDDING GIFT
THE GUCCIS GAVE US.

38:37.053 --> 38:38.185
COUPONS.

38:40.187 --> 38:41.797
FEELS LIKE CASH.

38:41.841 --> 38:43.103
I DOUBT IT.

38:46.976 --> 38:48.456
IT'S NOT CASH.

38:54.244 --> 38:55.855
FUCKING CONCORDE.

38:55.898 --> 38:57.117
TO WHERE?

38:58.205 --> 38:59.206
NEW YORK.

39:02.818 --> 39:04.472
NEW YORK.

39:04.516 --> 39:05.995
AH, PATRIZIA.

39:06.039 --> 39:08.694
WE CAN'T DRIVE TO NEW YORK,
WE HAVE TO FLY.

39:08.737 --> 39:10.565
YOU WANNA GO TO NEW YORK?

39:10.609 --> 39:12.045
NO.

39:12.088 --> 39:13.220
EVERYBODY LIKES NEW YORK.

39:14.090 --> 39:15.396
I DON'T.

39:15.440 --> 39:17.050
I WANNA GO TO NEW YORK.

39:17.093 --> 39:19.226
[GASPS] NEW YORK.

39:20.096 --> 39:22.098
I LOVE NEW YORK.

39:22.142 --> 39:23.578
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

39:23.622 --> 39:24.666
[PATRIZIA] NEW YORK.

39:26.929 --> 39:28.191
OKAY.

39:28.714 --> 39:29.715
OKAY.

39:46.514 --> 39:47.863
[SWITCHING ITALIAN CHANNELS]

39:56.916 --> 39:59.701
[WOMAN IN ENGLISH]
DO YOU HAVE MEDICAL MALADIES,
FINANCIAL WOES...

40:00.310 --> 40:02.443
HEARTBREAK?

40:02.487 --> 40:06.273
I CAN HELP YOU WITH
EVERYTHING AND ANYTHING.

40:07.143 --> 40:09.363
AND IT'S VERY, VERY PRIVATE.

40:10.190 --> 40:12.627
BECAUSE PINA IS DISCREET.

40:12.671 --> 40:14.412
AND VERY ACCURATE.

40:16.109 --> 40:18.677
YOU CAN COME TO ME
WITH ANY WORRIES.

40:18.720 --> 40:20.461
THERE IS NO NEED TO SUFFER.

40:20.505 --> 40:21.767
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

40:24.770 --> 40:26.859
HELLO, WHO AM I SPEAKING TO?

40:26.902 --> 40:28.121
-PATRIZIA.
-[DIALOGUE ECHOING ON TV]

40:28.164 --> 40:30.036
HOW OLD ARE YOU, DEAR?

40:30.079 --> 40:31.298
TWENTY-FIVE.

40:32.560 --> 40:34.388
TWENTY-FIVE.

40:34.432 --> 40:36.782
WHAT IS YOUR QUESTION,
PATRIZIA?

40:39.959 --> 40:41.395
WILL I BE SUCCESSFUL?

40:41.439 --> 40:43.789
YOU HAVE TO BE MORE SPECIFIC.

40:43.832 --> 40:46.574
IN WHAT?
CAREER, MARRIAGE, WHAT?

40:48.141 --> 40:49.403
WILL I GET WHAT I WANT?

40:50.448 --> 40:52.188
THAT WAS NOT SPECIFIC.

40:52.232 --> 40:54.321
BUT I KNOW WHAT YOU WANT.
YOU WANT EVERYTHING.

40:54.364 --> 40:56.932
WELL, DON'T BE DISAPPOINTED

40:56.976 --> 40:58.543
IF YOU DON'T HEAR
WHAT YOU WANT TO HEAR.

40:59.369 --> 41:00.370
OKAY.

41:01.981 --> 41:03.330
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

41:05.027 --> 41:06.333
MY NAME IS PINA.

41:07.813 --> 41:09.205
HELLO, PINA.

41:13.558 --> 41:14.907
TELL ME EVERYTHING.

41:17.213 --> 41:18.476
I SEE A GREAT FORTUNE...

41:19.346 --> 41:20.347
COMING YOUR WAY.

41:21.696 --> 41:22.784
HOW BIG?

41:24.220 --> 41:25.918
-SOPHIA! SOPHIA!
-SOPHIA!

41:25.961 --> 41:27.702
[POP MUSIC PLAYING]

41:28.660 --> 41:30.400
[REPORTERS CLAMORING]

41:40.759 --> 41:41.934
[REPORTERS CLAMORING]

41:57.689 --> 41:59.038
MAYBE, I'M NOT SURE.

41:59.081 --> 42:02.128
YES, WE HAVE SOMETHING.
I CAN SHOW YOU.

42:02.171 --> 42:03.912
MADEMOISELLE.

42:03.956 --> 42:05.653
ALL DUE RESPECT,

42:05.697 --> 42:08.482
THESE HEELS ARE
NOT RIGHT FOR YOU.

42:10.702 --> 42:11.616
HELLO, UNCLE.

42:12.791 --> 42:14.444
NO!

42:14.488 --> 42:17.273
WHAT ARE YOU DOING? PATRIZIA.

42:17.317 --> 42:19.101
-OH, MY!
-[GREETS IN ITALIAN]

42:19.145 --> 42:22.496
MY GORGEOUS NIECE. PATRIZIA.

42:23.845 --> 42:25.978
I WAS JUST IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

42:26.021 --> 42:28.807
-YES? IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD?
-I WAS HOPING I'D SEE YOU.

42:28.850 --> 42:31.331
MAURIZIO IS
A VERY SMART YOUNG MAN.

42:33.420 --> 42:36.423
SO HOW ARE THINGS
WITH HIS FATHER?

42:37.816 --> 42:39.426
NOT BAD, NOT GOOD.

42:39.469 --> 42:41.471
YEAH.

42:41.515 --> 42:44.431
MY BROTHER,
HE'S A DIFFICULT MAN.

42:46.085 --> 42:49.218
BUT IT'S TIME FOR THEM
TO RECONCILE.

42:49.262 --> 42:52.395
MAURIZIO AND HIS FATHER, NO?

42:52.439 --> 42:53.440
SI.

42:55.137 --> 42:57.618
MAURIZIO WANTS TO BE
PART OF THE FAMILY.

42:57.662 --> 42:59.272
I CAN SEE IT IN HIS EYES.

43:01.230 --> 43:02.362
BUT?

43:03.711 --> 43:05.713
BUT, HE NEEDS YOUR HELP.

43:05.757 --> 43:06.671
YEAH.

43:07.933 --> 43:09.935
WELL, HOW DO I HELP?

43:11.893 --> 43:13.808
MAYBE WE CAN
SPEND SOME TIME TOGETHER.

43:15.549 --> 43:16.855
YEAH, WHY NOT?

43:18.726 --> 43:19.814
DARLING UNCLE.

43:21.686 --> 43:22.469
MMM.

43:23.296 --> 43:24.514
MAURIZIO IS...

43:26.691 --> 43:27.822
HE'S PROUD.

43:29.084 --> 43:30.390
WE ALL ARE, DARLING.

43:31.739 --> 43:32.914
WE ALL ARE.

43:37.571 --> 43:39.312
[CATTLE LOWING]

43:41.488 --> 43:42.663
I LOVE IT.

43:43.185 --> 43:44.491
AH!

43:45.884 --> 43:49.496
MY DEAR, YOU SMELL THAT?
SMELL THAT!

43:50.715 --> 43:52.325
THIS IS LEGACY.

43:54.544 --> 43:56.459
THESE GORGEOUS BEASTS.

43:57.722 --> 44:00.550
DO YOU KNOW
THAT THESE GORGEOUS BEASTS

44:00.594 --> 44:02.683
ARE THE DIRECT DESCENDANTS

44:02.727 --> 44:05.512
OF THE ONES GUCCIO BOUGHT
WAY BACK WHEN?

44:06.382 --> 44:08.515
THEY DESERVE OUR RESPECT.

44:10.038 --> 44:11.649
THEY DESERVE OUR GRATITUDE.

44:12.606 --> 44:14.521
THEY ARE VAL DI CHIANA COWS.

44:18.177 --> 44:21.180
YES, YES. HELLO.

44:21.223 --> 44:22.747
[GREETING IN ITALIAN]

44:22.790 --> 44:25.793
I WANNA INTRODUCE YOU
TO MY NEPHEW MAURIZIO

44:25.837 --> 44:30.189
AND HIS BEAUTIFUL NEW BRIDE,
PATRIZIA.

44:30.232 --> 44:32.104
[GREETING IN ITALIAN]

44:32.147 --> 44:33.975
-HERE, TOUCH.
-WOW, THIS IS SOFT.

44:34.019 --> 44:35.890
SMELL IT TOO.
IT'S REALLY GREAT.

44:35.934 --> 44:37.631
LET ME SEE THIS NEW ONE.

44:51.645 --> 44:53.168
-BRAVO, BRAVO.
-BRAVO.

44:54.866 --> 44:58.565
I AM READY! I THINK
I BLOW 'EM OUT, RIGHT?

44:59.827 --> 45:00.654
[MUTTERS]

45:03.613 --> 45:05.572
COME ON! HELP ME
BLOW THESE OUT, PLEASE.

45:06.791 --> 45:08.140
I LIKE THIS PLACE.

45:09.271 --> 45:10.577
I LOVE THIS PLACE.

45:17.453 --> 45:19.281
AM I BORING YOU?

45:19.325 --> 45:21.022
-NO. NO.
-NO, NO. WE LOVE IT.

45:21.066 --> 45:22.763
MY WORD!

45:22.807 --> 45:26.027
BECAUSE I CAN'T TALK TO MY SON
PAOLO ABOUT ANY OF THIS.

45:26.071 --> 45:28.029
HE HATES GUCCI TALK.

45:28.073 --> 45:30.597
HE ONLY TALKS ABOUT HIMSELF.

45:32.120 --> 45:34.296
BUT AS YOU KNOW,
HE'S A STRANGE BIRD.

45:34.340 --> 45:36.603
MY SON IS A STRANGE BIRD.

45:37.735 --> 45:38.997
HE'S DEFINITELY UNIQUE.

45:40.520 --> 45:42.609
USELESS. SADLY.

45:44.132 --> 45:45.481
MAURIZIO!

45:45.525 --> 45:46.961
-YES?
-HOW ARE YOU?

45:47.005 --> 45:48.180
I'M GOOD.

45:48.223 --> 45:49.703
YOU HAD A GOOD DAY TODAY?

45:49.747 --> 45:51.270
IT WAS GOOD. I MEAN,
I SHOWED YOU EVERYTHING

45:51.313 --> 45:53.489
I COULD SHOW YOU
IN ONE SITTING.

45:53.533 --> 45:55.056
YES. THANK YOU
VERY MUCH, UNCLE.

45:55.100 --> 45:56.362
-I'M GLAD.
-IT'S BEAUTIFUL HERE.

45:56.405 --> 45:58.799
I SAY THIS BECAUSE PATRIZIA

45:58.843 --> 46:02.020
HAS TOLD ME THAT
YOU MAY BE INTERESTED...

46:02.063 --> 46:05.240
IN LEARNING ABOUT
OUR BUSINESS...

46:06.154 --> 46:07.286
WHATEVER.

46:10.245 --> 46:12.247
RODOLFO LOST A SON.

46:12.291 --> 46:14.641
MAYBE I GAIN ONE. RIGHT?

46:16.121 --> 46:17.339
SEE THAT.

46:23.955 --> 46:26.348
FAMILY IS IMPORTANT, MAURIZIO.

46:26.392 --> 46:28.829
YOU CAN'T ERASE YOURSELF
FROM THE FAMILY PORTRAIT...

46:28.873 --> 46:31.571
JUST BECAUSE YOU ENJOY
PLAYING WITH TRUCKS.

46:31.614 --> 46:33.660
THIS IS THE HAPPIEST
I'VE BEEN IN MY LIFE.

46:36.532 --> 46:37.664
WHY CHANGE THAT?

46:38.708 --> 46:39.666
YOU...

46:40.536 --> 46:42.321
YOU'RE SO MUCH MORE THAN THIS.

46:44.540 --> 46:46.020
YOU CAN HELP THE FAMILY.

46:47.805 --> 46:50.503
STRONG FAMILY MAKES
A STRONG BUSINESS.

47:09.914 --> 47:11.045
I'M PREGNANT.

47:17.617 --> 47:18.792
YOU'RE GONNA BE A FATHER.

47:22.143 --> 47:23.101
YOU'RE WHAT?

47:24.406 --> 47:25.712
I'M PREGNANT.

47:32.414 --> 47:33.763
WILL YOU HELP ME WITH...

47:33.807 --> 47:35.722
['80S POP MUSIC PLAYING]

48:25.337 --> 48:27.774
OH, OH!

48:27.817 --> 48:29.210
NOT MY CAMERA.

48:29.254 --> 48:31.604
-NOT THE CAMERA.
-NO. NO. NO.

48:31.647 --> 48:32.779
NOT THE SUIT.

48:33.998 --> 48:34.868
COME HERE.

48:36.043 --> 48:36.783
OOH!

48:39.046 --> 48:41.962
[LAUGHING] OH, MAURIZIO.
DON'T CATCH ON FIRE.

48:42.006 --> 48:42.789
[BOTH LAUGHING]

49:00.328 --> 49:01.286
DO YOU LIKE IT?

49:02.330 --> 49:03.766
THAT IS VERY BEAUTIFUL.

49:04.332 --> 49:05.420
IS THAT ON SALE?

49:06.117 --> 49:07.161
[LAUGHING]

49:07.205 --> 49:08.423
SALE.

49:09.207 --> 49:11.252
[ALDO] PATRIZIA!

49:12.210 --> 49:13.994
-CIAO, ALDO.
-MAURIZIO!

49:14.038 --> 49:16.431
-CIAO, ALDO.
-OH!

49:16.475 --> 49:20.087
MY YOUTH SERUM.
THAT'S WHAT YOU ARE.

49:20.131 --> 49:21.436
HOW DID YOU SLEEP?

49:21.480 --> 49:22.829
LIKE BABIES.

49:22.872 --> 49:24.657
THE SUITE IS UNREAL.
THANK YOU.

49:24.700 --> 49:25.832
WONDERFUL. WONDERFUL.

49:25.875 --> 49:27.355
-YOU LOOK GOOD.
-THANK YOU.

49:27.399 --> 49:28.878
BUT YOU...

49:28.922 --> 49:30.315
WELL, THAT LOOKS GREAT ON YOU.

49:31.533 --> 49:33.405
-GUCCI.
-GUCCI?

49:33.448 --> 49:34.710
LOOKS THAT GOOD!

49:35.450 --> 49:36.930
WE'RE SO SURPRISED.

49:36.974 --> 49:39.498
YEAH, PATRIZIA IS JUST
PLAYING DRESS-UP.

49:39.541 --> 49:43.284
YEAH. WELL,
HERE'S A LITTLE SECRET.

49:43.328 --> 49:46.113
DON'T TELL ANYBODY. SEE?

49:47.332 --> 49:48.768
COME HERE, PATRIZIA.

49:50.291 --> 49:51.945
I GOT SOMETHING
I WANT TO SHOW YOU.

49:51.989 --> 49:54.426
SORRY, MAURI,
DON'T TAKE IT PERSONALLY.

49:54.469 --> 49:57.907
ANYTHING YOU SEE IS YOURS.

49:57.951 --> 50:00.910
YOU WANT IT,
YOU SEE IT, IT'S YOURS.

50:00.954 --> 50:02.651
-FAMILY DISCOUNT.
-[MAN] MR. GUCCI!

50:03.435 --> 50:04.436
YES!

50:05.176 --> 50:06.264
EXCUSE ME.

50:07.569 --> 50:09.354
[GREETING IN JAPANESE]

50:15.142 --> 50:17.014
[ALDO] HI! HOW ARE YOU?

50:20.104 --> 50:21.714
[ALDO] SO WHAT DO YOU THINK?

50:21.757 --> 50:24.108
WHAT COULD YOU DO, MAURIZIO?

50:25.283 --> 50:26.371
AH, YES.

50:27.807 --> 50:28.851
-GRAZIE.
-GRAZIE.

50:30.114 --> 50:34.596
GUCCI WORLD AFFAIRS
COORDINATOR.

50:36.381 --> 50:37.686
WHAT?

50:37.730 --> 50:39.471
WHAT DOES THAT EVEN MEAN?

50:39.514 --> 50:41.560
I DON'T KNOW.
IT MEANS SOMETHING.

50:43.127 --> 50:46.086
YOU'LL BE MY EYES AND EARS
WHEN I'M AWAY.

50:46.130 --> 50:47.957
YOU'LL REPRESENT THE COMPANY.

50:49.655 --> 50:51.439
WITH FOREIGN BUYERS
OR ANYBODY ELSE.

50:52.658 --> 50:54.703
'CAUSE WITH YOUR KNOWLEDGE
OF THE LAW,

50:54.747 --> 50:55.922
YOUR LANGUAGE SKILLS...

50:57.445 --> 50:59.056
YOU FIT RIGHT IN.

50:59.099 --> 51:00.796
THANK YOU. WE'RE FLATTERED
AND WE'RE GRATEFUL.

51:00.840 --> 51:02.320
[ALDO] I'M GLAD.
I KNOW YOU ARE.

51:03.190 --> 51:04.322
YES?

51:05.149 --> 51:05.932
YES?

51:06.541 --> 51:08.195
[SIGHS]

51:08.239 --> 51:09.936
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

51:09.979 --> 51:12.591
I'M THINKING. I'M THINKING,
I'M THINKING...

51:12.634 --> 51:14.114
AND THINKING AND THINKING.

51:14.158 --> 51:15.942
I'M THINKING, I'LL CERTAINLY
THINK ABOUT IT.

51:18.379 --> 51:19.424
[IN ITALIAN]

51:39.835 --> 51:40.923
-FRANCO.
-MORNING, SIR.

51:40.967 --> 51:42.186
JUST IN TIME.

51:46.015 --> 51:47.539
HERE. HELP ME.

51:47.582 --> 51:48.757
YES, OF COURSE.

51:50.803 --> 51:51.847
BOOF.

51:58.289 --> 51:59.116
[DOOR CLOSES]

52:04.425 --> 52:05.600
HELLO, UNCLE.

52:06.210 --> 52:08.516
MY FAVORITE UNCLE.

52:08.560 --> 52:09.778
HELLO.

52:11.824 --> 52:12.825
WOW.

52:14.392 --> 52:16.176
SO SVELTE.

52:16.220 --> 52:18.047
[RODOLFO CHUCKLES]

52:18.091 --> 52:21.442
YOUR CHEEK BONES
COULD CUT A DIAMOND.

52:21.486 --> 52:25.185
OH, PLEASE. TO WHAT DO I OWE
THIS UNEXPECTED PLEASURE?

52:25.229 --> 52:29.798
WELL, I CAME
FIRST AND FOREMOST...

52:29.842 --> 52:33.019
TO SAY... WELL...

52:34.020 --> 52:34.890
HMM?

52:35.717 --> 52:36.718
HELLO.

52:37.502 --> 52:39.025
WELL, HELLO!

52:42.811 --> 52:45.031
UH, WAS THERE ANYTHING ELSE?

52:45.945 --> 52:47.033
[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

52:48.904 --> 52:51.516
MAURIZIO AND MY FATHER
HAVE BEEN SPENDING

52:51.559 --> 52:53.213
A LOT OF TIME TOGETHER
IN NEW YORK.

52:53.257 --> 52:55.041
AND I THOUGHT...

52:56.782 --> 52:58.914
MAYBE YOU AND I
COULD DO THE SAME.

52:59.698 --> 53:01.656
WHY WOULD I...

53:01.700 --> 53:03.180
[PAOLO] WELL, TO DISCUSS...

53:04.268 --> 53:05.791
[RODOLFO] TO DISCUSS WHAT?

53:05.834 --> 53:07.271
MY IDEAS.

53:08.489 --> 53:10.970
-YOU HAVE IDEAS?
-BOOF.

53:11.013 --> 53:13.538
DOES AN ELEPHANT
SHIT IN THE JUNGLE?

53:15.192 --> 53:18.064
I WAS BORN WITH A GIFT.

53:19.370 --> 53:21.110
I AM AN ARTIST.

53:21.154 --> 53:23.243
MY FATHER,
HE JUST WON'T SEE IT.

53:24.592 --> 53:25.245
BUT...

53:26.855 --> 53:28.640
THESE ARE YOURS?

53:28.683 --> 53:31.686
HOW COME THE FAMILY
DOESN'T KNOW
YOU HAVE A GIFT?

53:31.730 --> 53:33.906
DOMENICO, DID YOU KNOW
PAOLO HAD A GIFT?

53:33.949 --> 53:36.082
I'M AFRAID I DID NOT, SIR.

53:36.125 --> 53:38.171
WELL, WE BOTH KNOW
HE'S BLIND IN ONE EYE

53:38.215 --> 53:39.912
AND DEAF IN THE OTHER. SO.

53:41.740 --> 53:43.176
-THIS IS...
-OH, WAIT.

53:43.220 --> 53:46.266
LET ME SHOW YOU.
[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

53:46.310 --> 53:50.314
THESE WERE INSPIRED
BY MY TRIP TO CUBA.

53:50.357 --> 53:52.185
I CALL THIS COLLECTION...

53:53.317 --> 53:54.883
"HAVANA LIBRE."

53:58.322 --> 54:00.106
LOTS OF PASTELS.

54:00.149 --> 54:04.589
RUM INSPIRED, SUN-SOAKED
AND LOTS OF BROWNS.

54:04.632 --> 54:10.682
YOU HAVE PASTELS
AND BROWN TOGETHER.

54:10.725 --> 54:12.510
YES, YES, YES.

54:12.553 --> 54:14.468
I KNOW, IT'S MUSICAL.

54:21.432 --> 54:22.520
PAOLO.

54:22.563 --> 54:23.608
YEAH.

54:25.305 --> 54:28.134
YOU MUST NOT SHOW THESE
TO ANYONE.

54:29.614 --> 54:30.745
KEEP THEM HIDDEN.

54:31.920 --> 54:32.878
I MEAN IT.

54:34.271 --> 54:37.317
YOU FEEL THEY MIGHT STEAL
MY IDEAS, RIGHT?

54:37.361 --> 54:40.799
OH, CALL ME A LAWYER.

54:40.842 --> 54:42.017
NOT YOU.

54:44.106 --> 54:46.152
OVER THE YEARS, I HAVE FOUND...

54:48.285 --> 54:54.639
THAT TRUE TALENT
IS OFTEN UNAWARE
OF ITS OWN BRILLIANCE.

54:54.682 --> 54:59.339
IT MUST BE CHERISHED
AND PROTECTED.

54:59.383 --> 55:01.950
WHEREAS HACKS,
THEY RUN AROUND...

55:03.300 --> 55:08.130
SHOUTING THEIR
DELICIOUS IDEAS,

55:08.174 --> 55:10.568
BEGGING TO BE RECOGNIZED.

55:10.611 --> 55:11.743
BLIND...

55:13.397 --> 55:14.789
TO THEIR OWN...

55:17.226 --> 55:18.358
MEDIOCRITY.

55:22.362 --> 55:24.059
MY DEAR NEPHEW,
YOU HAVE ACHIEVED

55:26.018 --> 55:29.326
A TRIUMPH OF MEDIOCRITY.

55:31.676 --> 55:34.766
AND YOU HAVE ALSO ACHIEVED
THE UNIMAGINABLE.

55:36.420 --> 55:38.335
YOU HAVE FOUND ONE THING...

55:39.727 --> 55:44.079
UPON WHICH YOUR FATHER AND I
CAN AGREE.

55:45.951 --> 55:50.390
YOUR TOTAL INCOMPETENCE.

55:54.133 --> 55:55.656
OH, NO.

55:57.354 --> 55:58.355
FORGIVE ME.

56:01.749 --> 56:02.794
BUT I...

56:05.057 --> 56:06.319
I HAVE TO TAKE A MEETING.

56:11.193 --> 56:13.587
YOU DESIGNED THIS SCARF,
CORRECT?

56:13.631 --> 56:14.588
OH, YES.

56:16.198 --> 56:18.810
THAT SCARF IS MY SIGNATURE.

56:18.853 --> 56:21.856
IT HAS CARESSED THE NECKS
OF ALL THE WORLD'S BEAUTIES.

56:21.900 --> 56:24.424
JACKIE O, GRACE, SOFIA.

56:26.774 --> 56:28.080
STUDY IT CLOSELY.

56:29.386 --> 56:32.301
NO BROWNS, NO PASTELS.

56:34.173 --> 56:35.261
-COME.
-YES.

56:43.878 --> 56:45.271
[DOOR CLOSES]

56:55.150 --> 56:57.326
I DON'T NEED ANYONE.

56:59.067 --> 57:01.505
I'M PAOLO.

57:01.548 --> 57:02.941
PAOLO GUCCI.

57:05.378 --> 57:07.075
AND I AM GOING TO START...

57:08.729 --> 57:10.165
MY OWN LINE.

57:16.345 --> 57:17.999
[BABY COOING]

57:31.448 --> 57:32.449
MR. GUCCI.

57:34.581 --> 57:36.975
-ARE YOU OKAY?
-SI, SI.

57:39.978 --> 57:41.327
[BABY FUSSES]

57:41.762 --> 57:42.937
GRAZIE.

57:51.946 --> 57:53.339
MY FATHER IS ILL.

58:13.751 --> 58:15.622
-CIAO, FRANCO.
-CIAO, FRANCO.

58:15.666 --> 58:16.797
MAURIZIO.

58:17.450 --> 58:19.365
[COUGHING]

58:28.679 --> 58:30.376
EXCUSE ME. EXCUSE ME.

58:35.947 --> 58:37.383
WHAT IS THIS?

58:43.650 --> 58:44.869
I'M A GRANDFATHER?

58:49.787 --> 58:51.397
[PATRIZIA]
HER NAME IS ALESSANDRA.

58:52.877 --> 58:54.487
LIKE MAURIZIO'S MOTHER.

58:58.839 --> 59:00.319
WHOSE IDEA WAS THAT?

59:04.453 --> 59:05.803
MINE.

59:05.846 --> 59:06.586
WELL...

59:09.110 --> 59:10.416
ALESSANDRA.

59:11.069 --> 59:12.418
HERE. COME HERE.

59:12.461 --> 59:14.115
COME, COME, COME.

59:19.251 --> 59:20.426
MY BOY.

59:37.617 --> 59:39.488
YOU TAKE CARE OF GUCCI NOW.
HMM?

59:42.840 --> 59:44.406
I'M GLAD IT WASN'T A BOY.

59:45.451 --> 59:47.627
WE NEED MORE WOMEN
IN THIS FAMILY.

1:00:07.081 --> 1:00:08.909
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

1:00:12.347 --> 1:00:14.523
THERE IS NO LOVE ON EARTH

1:00:14.567 --> 1:00:17.483
GREATER THAN THAT OF A FATHER
FOR HIS SON.

1:00:20.529 --> 1:00:22.096
WITH A FEW EXCEPTIONS.

1:00:24.403 --> 1:00:26.361
THANK YOU FOR COMING, UNCLE.

1:00:26.405 --> 1:00:29.495
COME TO NEW YORK.
JOIN THE FAMILY.

1:00:31.149 --> 1:00:32.629
MAKE HIM PROUD.

1:00:36.197 --> 1:00:37.503
I'LL THINK ABOUT IT.

1:00:37.546 --> 1:00:38.504
YEAH.

1:00:50.908 --> 1:00:52.387
[DOMENICO]
THE HOUSE IN ST. MORITZ.

1:00:53.650 --> 1:00:55.695
TWO BEACH HOUSES,
ONE IN NASSAU,

1:00:55.739 --> 1:00:56.957
THE OTHER IN TAORMINA.

1:00:57.654 --> 1:00:59.003
TWENTY-THREE HORSES.

1:01:00.787 --> 1:01:03.877
PENTHOUSE APARTMENT
IN GALLERIA PASSARELLA...

1:01:03.921 --> 1:01:05.879
THE ONLY ONE IN ALL OF MILAN
WITH A SWIMMING POOL.

1:01:07.751 --> 1:01:11.102
AND, OF COURSE,
50% OF GUCCI S.P.A.

1:01:13.234 --> 1:01:17.151
BUT... THERE IS
A SLIGHT COMPLICATION.

1:01:19.197 --> 1:01:24.942
HE, RODOLFO, HE NEVER SIGNED
THE SHARE CERTIFICATE.

1:01:36.649 --> 1:01:37.694
[MAURIZIO]
OKAY, WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

1:01:39.217 --> 1:01:40.566
[DOMENICO]
YOU'LL HAVE TO PAY
INHERITANCE TAX.

1:01:41.306 --> 1:01:42.394
OH, THAT'S FINE.

1:01:43.395 --> 1:01:44.483
HOW MUCH ARE WE TALKING?

1:01:46.180 --> 1:01:48.617
[DOMENICO] COULD BE AS HIGH
AS 14 BILLION LIRE.

1:01:48.661 --> 1:01:50.358
-[MAURIZIO] 14 BILLION?
-YEAH.

1:01:50.402 --> 1:01:51.838
I CAN'T AFFORD THAT.

1:01:53.622 --> 1:01:55.755
WELL, YOU COULD
SELL YOUR SHARES.

1:01:55.799 --> 1:01:58.192
[MAURIZIO] TO WHO?

1:01:58.236 --> 1:02:00.586
-I CAN THINK OF
A FEW QUALIFIED INDIVIDUALS.
-THANK YOU.

1:02:00.629 --> 1:02:02.980
LEAVE THEM WITH US.

1:02:03.023 --> 1:02:04.938
WE'LL REVIEW THEM
AS SOON AS WE'RE DONE MOURNING.

1:02:05.722 --> 1:02:06.679
OF COURSE.

1:02:09.551 --> 1:02:11.249
WHO DOES HE THINK HE IS?

1:02:11.292 --> 1:02:13.381
SUGGESTING YOU SELL
YOUR SHARES.

1:02:13.425 --> 1:02:14.905
MADNESS.

1:02:14.948 --> 1:02:17.255
FOURTEEN BILLION IS TOTALLY
UNREASONABLE.

1:02:17.298 --> 1:02:20.040
AND JUST BECAUSE YOUR FATHER
FORGOT TO SIGN IT.

1:02:37.362 --> 1:02:41.192
[GIUSEPPINA]
TEN OF SPADES REPRESENTS
THEFT OR LOSS.

1:02:42.584 --> 1:02:45.457
SOMEONE WANTS WHAT IS YOURS.

1:02:45.500 --> 1:02:46.632
DON'T LET THEM TAKE IT.

1:02:47.459 --> 1:02:49.983
AND DON'T TRUST ANYBODY.

1:02:50.027 --> 1:02:54.379
BECAUSE I SEE
AN ABUSE OF TRUST.

1:02:54.422 --> 1:02:57.643
AN ATTEMPT TO DECEIVE YOU
IN YOUR OWN HOUSE.
YOU UNDERSTAND?

1:02:58.905 --> 1:03:00.907
YES, PINA.

1:03:00.951 --> 1:03:04.041
ALWAYS HAVE SOMETHING RED
ON YOU FOR PROTECTION.

1:03:04.084 --> 1:03:07.131
AND WEAR MORE GREEN.
GREEN IS FOR CLEANSING.

1:03:10.699 --> 1:03:11.875
GREEN DOESN'T GO
WITH MY LIPSTICK.

1:03:13.572 --> 1:03:15.400
-CHANGE YOUR LIPSTICK.
-[PATRIZIA LAUGHS]

1:03:15.443 --> 1:03:17.315
YOU'RE ALREADY SO BEAUTIFUL.

1:03:17.358 --> 1:03:18.664
OR WEAR GREEN UNDERWEAR.

1:03:20.187 --> 1:03:22.276
MAYBE IT'S TIME FOR YOU
TO TAKE BACK.

1:03:24.104 --> 1:03:27.760
DON'T LET THESE FORCES
AROUND YOU DICTATE WHO YOU ARE.

1:03:27.804 --> 1:03:31.068
YOU'RE STRONG.
YOU'RE MAGNIFICENT.

1:03:31.111 --> 1:03:32.243
AND...

1:03:34.898 --> 1:03:36.464
HMM, LOOK AT THIS.

1:03:38.379 --> 1:03:40.599
THERE'S A GREAT LOVE
IN YOUR LIFE.

1:03:44.168 --> 1:03:48.520
TOGETHER, YOU CAN CONQUER
THE WORLD.

1:03:50.827 --> 1:03:52.132
PATRIZIA, LOOK AT ME.

1:03:53.655 --> 1:03:55.701
YOU WILL BE THE QUEEN.
YOU.

1:03:58.573 --> 1:03:59.923
["I FEEL LOVE" PLAYING]

1:04:08.496 --> 1:04:09.323
HI!

1:04:10.498 --> 1:04:12.500
WHAT A BEAUTY.

1:04:12.544 --> 1:04:13.719
WHAT A BEAUTY.

1:04:13.762 --> 1:04:15.068
SO GOOD TO SEE YOU.

1:04:15.112 --> 1:04:15.852
COME. COME.

1:04:16.548 --> 1:04:18.332
MUCH TO SHOW YOU.

1:04:20.595 --> 1:04:23.860
THIS IS YOUR NEW OFFICE.

1:04:24.382 --> 1:04:25.513
WOW.

1:04:25.557 --> 1:04:26.906
I'M ACROSS THE HALL.

1:04:28.386 --> 1:04:29.735
IF YOU NEED ME.

1:04:30.388 --> 1:04:32.129
OKAY.

1:04:33.608 --> 1:04:35.741
LOOK. ENJOY.

1:04:35.784 --> 1:04:37.351
-THANK YOU.
-CIAO, ALDO.

1:04:37.395 --> 1:04:38.396
[ALDO] CIAO.

1:04:43.488 --> 1:04:44.619
[PATRIZIA CHUCKLES]

1:05:12.560 --> 1:05:14.127
I GOT PANE FRESCO.

1:05:16.042 --> 1:05:18.784
IF YOU DIDN'T EAT BREAKFAST,
YOUR FATHER'S GONNA BE
VERY UPSET WITH YOU.

1:05:36.367 --> 1:05:37.411
IRA?

1:05:38.369 --> 1:05:39.370
[IRA] YES?

1:05:40.110 --> 1:05:41.067
IRA, IS THIS YOURS?

1:05:42.242 --> 1:05:43.635
YES.

1:05:43.678 --> 1:05:46.203
BIRTHDAY GIFT.
FROM MY HUSBAND.

1:05:47.247 --> 1:05:48.379
IT'S A GUCCI.

1:05:49.119 --> 1:05:50.424
JUST LIKE YOURS.

1:05:52.470 --> 1:05:54.994
WHICH GUCCI STORE DID HE GO TO?

1:05:56.300 --> 1:05:57.823
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

1:06:20.933 --> 1:06:22.108
[PATRIZIA] WHO IS
MAKING THIS STUFF?

1:06:24.502 --> 1:06:25.851
WHO'S ALLOWING THIS TO HAPPEN?

1:06:27.461 --> 1:06:29.681
AS FAR AS FAKES GO,
THEY'RE PRETTY GOOD.

1:06:29.724 --> 1:06:30.856
I MEAN, I'D BUY THEM.
[CHUCKLES]

1:06:31.683 --> 1:06:32.858
DON'T BE SUCH A CRETIN.

1:06:37.123 --> 1:06:38.820
DON'T CALL ME
A CRETIN, SWEETIE.

1:06:40.257 --> 1:06:44.043
THAT'S NOT WHAT I SAID.
I ASKED YOU NOT TO BE ONE.

1:06:44.087 --> 1:06:47.438
THIS IS SERIOUS
AND YOU'RE LAUGHING IT OFF.

1:06:47.481 --> 1:06:49.875
AT LEAST IT'S MY NAME
ON THE MUGS, NOT YOURS.

1:06:51.094 --> 1:06:53.313
OUR NAME, SWEETIE.

1:06:54.401 --> 1:06:55.359
ON JUNK!

1:07:00.929 --> 1:07:02.366
[ALDO] THEY'RE NOT FAKE,
BY THE WAY.

1:07:03.541 --> 1:07:05.717
THEY'RE REPLICAS.

1:07:05.760 --> 1:07:07.762
I WAS JUST VERY,
VERY SURPRISED.

1:07:10.243 --> 1:07:12.158
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT ELSE
WOULD SURPRISE YOU?

1:07:14.726 --> 1:07:17.337
HOW PROFITABLE THIS STUFF IS.

1:07:17.381 --> 1:07:18.338
WHAT ABOUT QUALITY?

1:07:19.513 --> 1:07:21.776
YOUR SACRED COWS?

1:07:21.820 --> 1:07:23.952
[ALDO] QUALITY IS FOR THE RICH.

1:07:25.084 --> 1:07:28.696
IF A LONG ISLAND HOUSEWIFE
WANTS TO...

1:07:28.740 --> 1:07:33.397
LIVE WITH THE ILLUSION THAT
SHE IS A GUCCI CUSTOMER...

1:07:34.354 --> 1:07:36.400
WHY NOT? LET HER.

1:07:36.443 --> 1:07:39.316
BECAUSE IT DAMAGES
GUCCI'S CREDIBILITY.

1:07:40.273 --> 1:07:42.928
PATRIZIA, THIS IS US.

1:07:45.061 --> 1:07:46.845
THIS IS NOT A GIRL'S GAME.

1:07:50.240 --> 1:07:52.068
[MAURIZIO] YEAH, BUT, ALDO,
SHE'S RIGHT.

1:07:53.025 --> 1:07:55.593
THIS STUFF IS JUNK.

1:07:56.855 --> 1:07:58.378
IT'S NOT WHAT GUCCI IS.

1:07:59.249 --> 1:08:00.293
GUCCI...

1:08:02.556 --> 1:08:04.167
IS WHAT I SAY IT IS.

1:08:07.431 --> 1:08:10.129
I TURNED IT INTO AN EMPIRE.

1:08:10.173 --> 1:08:12.566
NOT RODOLFO.

1:08:12.610 --> 1:08:14.090
CERTAINLY NOT MY SON.

1:08:15.047 --> 1:08:15.961
AND, UH...

1:08:17.658 --> 1:08:20.748
OF COURSE, NOT YOU, SO...

1:08:23.664 --> 1:08:25.275
WITHOUT ME...

1:08:25.318 --> 1:08:30.323
YOU'D ALL STILL BE
SHOVELING COW SHIT IN TUSCANY.

1:08:32.456 --> 1:08:33.761
THAT'S A FACT.

1:08:37.417 --> 1:08:38.331
REMEMBER THAT.

1:08:40.072 --> 1:08:43.597
WE SHOULD REMEMBER THAT.

1:08:43.641 --> 1:08:45.251
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

1:08:50.300 --> 1:08:51.823
BRAVA!

1:08:51.866 --> 1:08:52.998
[WOMAN] BRAVO! BRAVO!

1:08:54.130 --> 1:08:56.610
[AUDIENCE CHEERING]

1:09:06.794 --> 1:09:07.795
A MARTINI, PLEASE.

1:09:07.839 --> 1:09:08.622
[BARTENDER] YES, SIR.

1:09:09.319 --> 1:09:10.189
DID YOU LIKE THE SHOW?

1:09:12.496 --> 1:09:14.019
OH, IT WAS INCREDIBLE.

1:09:14.062 --> 1:09:17.675
THE... THE...
THE LINES AND TONES.

1:09:17.718 --> 1:09:18.719
WELL, WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

1:09:19.546 --> 1:09:20.199
MY NAME?

1:09:23.246 --> 1:09:24.377
MAURIZIO.

1:09:25.335 --> 1:09:26.205
MAURIZIO WHAT?

1:09:28.120 --> 1:09:28.990
MAURIZIO GUCCI.

1:09:30.253 --> 1:09:33.343
MAURIZIO GUCCI.
HOW ABOUT THAT? GUCCI.

1:09:33.386 --> 1:09:34.779
YOU KNOW, I USED TO
DRESS WINDOWS FOR GUCCI.

1:09:34.822 --> 1:09:36.302
OH, REALLY? WHICH STORE?

1:09:37.869 --> 1:09:39.218
I CAN'T REMEMBER. IT WAS...

1:09:39.262 --> 1:09:40.785
IT WAS GOD-AWFUL THOUGH.

1:09:41.438 --> 1:09:42.700
WALTER, BY THE WAY.

1:09:42.743 --> 1:09:44.049
I'M A DESIGNER.

1:09:45.529 --> 1:09:46.834
OKAY, WALTER.

1:09:48.314 --> 1:09:51.099
WELL, MAYBE YOU WILL DESIGN
FOR ME SOMEDAY.

1:09:51.143 --> 1:09:53.624
NO. NO DESIGNER HERE'S GONNA
WORK FOR GUCCI.

1:09:54.886 --> 1:09:56.192
RIGHT NOW, GUCCI...

1:09:57.105 --> 1:09:58.672
GUCCI'S JUST A CHEAP OPERETTA.

1:10:03.155 --> 1:10:04.896
-GRAZIA.
-SALUD.

1:10:05.853 --> 1:10:07.290
WELL, ENJOY YOURSELF.

1:10:15.907 --> 1:10:17.213
DO YOU WANT TO BE LEFT
IN THE DUST?

1:10:18.562 --> 1:10:21.260
YOU WANT TO KEEP SELLING
COFFEE MUGS IN AIRPORTS?

1:10:22.130 --> 1:10:23.523
IS THAT YOUR LEGACY?

1:10:28.049 --> 1:10:29.660
IT'S TIME TO
TAKE OUT THE TRASH.

1:10:31.357 --> 1:10:34.578
ALDO AND PAOLO, THEY'RE POISON.

1:10:34.621 --> 1:10:36.884
THEY'RE AN EMBARRASSMENT
TO THIS COMPANY...

1:10:37.929 --> 1:10:39.017
AND EVERYBODY KNOWS IT.

1:10:40.584 --> 1:10:41.367
THEY HAVE TO GO.

1:10:43.326 --> 1:10:45.110
AND YOU NEED TO GET
YOUR FUCKING BUSINESS
ORGANIZED.

1:10:46.503 --> 1:10:47.330
[MAURIZIO] PATRIZIA...

1:10:49.680 --> 1:10:50.985
THEY'RE MY FAMILY.

1:10:53.727 --> 1:10:54.859
[EXHALES]

1:10:54.902 --> 1:10:55.729
SO AM I.

1:10:57.383 --> 1:10:59.559
HE'S STARTING A TRADE WAR.

1:10:59.603 --> 1:11:02.127
PAOLO BARELY HAS ENOUGH
TO BANKROLL A PAIR OF SOCKS,

1:11:02.170 --> 1:11:03.607
LET ALONE START A WAR
WITH ANYONE.

1:11:03.650 --> 1:11:05.304
I DON'T WANT TO SEE IT.

1:11:05.348 --> 1:11:07.132
[DOMENICO] YES, BUT HE COULD
STILL BE A PROBLEM.

1:11:07.175 --> 1:11:10.266
ALDO HAS AWARDED HIM A NUMBER
OF SHARES IN THE COMPANY.

1:11:10.309 --> 1:11:12.485
YES, BUT ALDO DIDN'T REALIZE
WHAT AN IDIOT

1:11:12.529 --> 1:11:14.095
PAOLO TURNED OUT TO BE.

1:11:14.139 --> 1:11:16.359
MAURIZIO, WE NEED
TO BUILD A BRIDGE

1:11:16.402 --> 1:11:17.969
WITH PAOLO AND WORK THINGS OUT.

1:11:18.883 --> 1:11:20.624
YOU KNOW HOW EMOTIONAL HE GETS.

1:11:20.667 --> 1:11:23.235
HE'S AROUND
ALL THIS MALE ENERGY
ALL THE TIME.

1:11:23.279 --> 1:11:25.019
HIS WIFE ISN'T EXACTLY
THE BRIGHTEST.

1:11:25.063 --> 1:11:27.152
HE NEEDS SOMEONE
HE CAN TALK TO,

1:11:27.195 --> 1:11:28.414
WHO HE TRUSTS,
WHO LISTENS TO HIM.

1:11:29.720 --> 1:11:30.764
SOMEONE LIKE WHO?

1:11:32.288 --> 1:11:33.158
[LAUGHS]

1:11:34.768 --> 1:11:36.814
-PAOLO LIKES ME.
-[DOMENICO SCOFFS]

1:11:36.857 --> 1:11:37.989
YOU DO HAVE
A NATURAL ADVANTAGE.

1:11:38.032 --> 1:11:39.164
YOU ARE NOT A GUCCI.

1:11:43.255 --> 1:11:44.169
I...

1:11:45.779 --> 1:11:47.172
I NEED AN ESPRESSO.

1:11:55.398 --> 1:11:56.834
CAN I ASK YOU A QUESTION?

1:11:58.401 --> 1:11:59.184
YOU JUST DID.

1:12:00.446 --> 1:12:01.273
HUH?

1:12:02.622 --> 1:12:03.884
YOU JUST ASKED ME A QUESTION.

1:12:05.364 --> 1:12:06.713
AND WHAT YOU REALLY
WANT TO KNOW IS

1:12:06.757 --> 1:12:08.106
WHETHER YOU CAN ASK ME
TWO QUESTIONS,

1:12:08.149 --> 1:12:09.455
ONE OF WHICH
YOU'VE ALREADY ASKED.

1:12:09.499 --> 1:12:11.805
[LAUGHING]

1:12:11.849 --> 1:12:15.679
THAT'S GOOD.
DOMENICO, VERY FUNNY.

1:12:15.722 --> 1:12:17.420
OKAY, HERE IS
MY SECOND QUESTION.

1:12:19.465 --> 1:12:24.427
WHAT DO YOU SEE AS BEING
YOUR PURPOSE AT GUCCI?

1:12:26.690 --> 1:12:27.778
IS THIS A JOB INTERVIEW?

1:12:28.256 --> 1:12:29.214
MAYBE.

1:12:31.085 --> 1:12:32.565
I'M A CONSERVATIONIST.

1:12:34.567 --> 1:12:37.875
GUCCI IS A RARE ANIMAL.
IT MUST BE PROTECTED.

1:12:39.833 --> 1:12:40.834
PROTECTED FROM WHO?

1:12:42.096 --> 1:12:43.402
FROM WHOEVER THREATENS IT.

1:12:45.622 --> 1:12:48.059
I FIND IT VERY INTERESTING THAT

1:12:48.102 --> 1:12:50.278
YOU HAVE SUCH
A STRONG CONNECTION

1:12:50.322 --> 1:12:52.585
TO THAT WHICH IS NOT YOURS.

1:12:54.152 --> 1:12:56.241
UH...

1:12:56.284 --> 1:12:58.635
SOMETIMES IT TAKES AN OUTSIDER
TO SEE THE TRUTH.

1:12:59.113 --> 1:13:00.071
BRAVO.

1:13:01.855 --> 1:13:06.251
PAOLO, THIS ONE REMINDS ME
OF CHILDHOOD.

1:13:06.294 --> 1:13:10.298
YEAH, WELL, IT'S A MEMORY
WRAPPED IN LYCRA.

1:13:10.342 --> 1:13:13.998
IT'S JUST SO YOU.
IT'S EXQUISITE.

1:13:14.041 --> 1:13:15.434
DO YOU THINK SO?

1:13:15.478 --> 1:13:17.044
YOU HAVE A GIFT,
I'M TELLING YOU.

1:13:17.088 --> 1:13:18.350
OH, WELL, STOP.

1:13:19.351 --> 1:13:21.266
STOP, YOU'RE GOING
TO MAKE ME...

1:13:21.309 --> 1:13:23.268
YOU'RE GOING TO MAKE ME CRY.

1:13:24.574 --> 1:13:28.839
NOBODY HAS EVER
SAID THAT TO ME. NOBODY.

1:13:28.882 --> 1:13:31.145
PAOLO, WHY DON'T YOU HAVE
YOUR OWN LINE?

1:13:31.189 --> 1:13:34.279
THESE ARE JUST MOCK-UPS.

1:13:34.322 --> 1:13:37.108
I CAN'T AFFORD TO GET SERIOUS.

1:13:37.151 --> 1:13:38.892
WITH YOUR GIFT,
AND YOUR TALENT,

1:13:38.936 --> 1:13:39.850
AND YOUR VISION...

1:13:39.893 --> 1:13:40.938
ARE YOU KIDDING?

1:13:40.981 --> 1:13:42.418
GUCCI NEEDS NEW BLOOD.

1:13:43.288 --> 1:13:44.768
GOODBYE 1930S.

1:13:45.725 --> 1:13:48.075
HELLO, '80S. HUH?

1:13:48.119 --> 1:13:51.862
OH, YOU TOOK THE WORDS
RIGHT OUT OF MY GUTS.

1:13:51.905 --> 1:13:53.646
-PAOLO GUCCI IS COMING.
-[PAOLO SCATTING]

1:13:57.433 --> 1:14:00.000
COME ON. [CONTINUES SCATTING]

1:14:03.569 --> 1:14:04.309
[GROANS]

1:14:05.353 --> 1:14:06.311
[SIGHS]

1:14:10.620 --> 1:14:13.187
I'M DISGUSTED BY THE WAY
YOUR FATHER TREATS YOU.

1:14:14.450 --> 1:14:15.320
[SIGHS]

1:14:16.713 --> 1:14:19.150
LEAVING YOU BEHIND
TO GROOM MAURIZIO.

1:14:20.020 --> 1:14:21.674
IT'S NOT RIGHT.

1:14:21.718 --> 1:14:23.023
WHO DOES HE THINK HE IS?

1:14:24.242 --> 1:14:27.898
WELL, A DINOSAUR POSING
AS A BUTTHOLE.

1:14:27.941 --> 1:14:29.900
[CHUCKLES]

1:14:29.943 --> 1:14:32.119
[LAUGHING]

1:14:32.163 --> 1:14:33.991
YOU WERE A COMEDIAN
IN A PAST LIFE.

1:14:35.819 --> 1:14:37.342
[PAOLO WHEEZING]

1:14:38.169 --> 1:14:39.823
MAURIZIO LIKES YOU.

1:14:39.866 --> 1:14:41.955
-[PAOLO] AH...
-HE ALWAYS HAS.

1:14:41.999 --> 1:14:44.567
WELL, I LIKE MY COUSIN TOO.

1:14:44.610 --> 1:14:48.962
HE'S QUIET LIKE A...
LIKE A LITTLE MOUSE.

1:14:49.006 --> 1:14:51.138
UH, TINY LITTLE MOUSY.

1:14:51.182 --> 1:14:53.576
DOESN'T SCREAM LIKE THE OTHERS.

1:14:53.619 --> 1:14:56.970
NO, HE DOESN'T. AND YOU
AND MAURIZIO TOGETHER...

1:14:57.014 --> 1:14:58.885
THAT WOULD BE AMAZING.

1:14:58.929 --> 1:15:01.192
-THAT'S A NEW
CHAPTER FOR GUCCI.
-[PAOLO] NO, NO, NO.

1:15:01.235 --> 1:15:03.977
MY FATHER,
HE WOULD NEVER ALLOW IT.

1:15:04.021 --> 1:15:07.459
HE'S GOT MY LITTLE PEACHES
IN A VERY TIGHT GRIP.

1:15:08.068 --> 1:15:09.156
PAOLO...

1:15:11.376 --> 1:15:12.595
MAYBE IT'S TIME...

1:15:14.031 --> 1:15:15.423
TO RESPECTFULLY...

1:15:17.382 --> 1:15:18.601
LEAVE HIM BEHIND.

1:15:20.994 --> 1:15:22.387
YOU ARE JUSTIFIED.

1:15:25.956 --> 1:15:30.047
I DO HAVE...

1:15:31.048 --> 1:15:33.006
SOMETHING ON MY FATHER.

1:15:34.442 --> 1:15:38.229
CAN YOU KEEP A SECRET?

1:15:38.272 --> 1:15:40.405
CROSS YOUR HEART
AND HOPE TO DIE.

1:15:42.450 --> 1:15:45.845
FATHER, SON,
AND HOUSE OF GUCCI.

1:15:45.889 --> 1:15:46.977
[PAOLO] OKAY.

1:15:48.761 --> 1:15:49.849
OKAY.

1:15:57.422 --> 1:15:59.467
WELL, YOU KNOW...

1:15:59.511 --> 1:16:00.599
[PATRIZIA] YOU DON'T
HAVE TO TELL ME.

1:16:00.643 --> 1:16:02.427
-LISTEN...
-IT'S JUST...

1:16:02.470 --> 1:16:04.429
I CAN COME BACK ANY TIME.
WE CAN TALK ABOUT YOUR DESIGNS.

1:16:06.083 --> 1:16:10.087
BUT WHAT WOULD I GET
OUT OF THIS?

1:16:17.921 --> 1:16:20.576
WE COULD OFFER YOU
AN EXCLUSIVE DEAL

1:16:20.619 --> 1:16:22.578
TO DISTRIBUTE YOUR OWN LINE
UNDER GUCCI.

1:16:23.970 --> 1:16:25.537
I SHOULD TALK TO MAURIZIO.

1:16:31.543 --> 1:16:32.588
[MAURIZIO] YOU TALKED TO HIM?

1:16:33.240 --> 1:16:34.415
WHEN?

1:16:34.459 --> 1:16:35.416
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1:16:35.460 --> 1:16:37.070
TODAY.

1:16:37.114 --> 1:16:38.594
HE SHOWED ME HIS DESIGNS.

1:16:39.377 --> 1:16:40.596
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME?

1:16:41.988 --> 1:16:43.860
[PATRIZIA] I'M TELLING YOU NOW,
AREN'T I?

1:16:43.903 --> 1:16:45.905
[SPUTTERS] PATRIZIA,
THAT'S NOT THE POINT.

1:16:45.949 --> 1:16:49.082
DON'T FOCUS ON THE PROCESS,
FOCUS ON THE RESULT.

1:16:50.910 --> 1:16:52.869
I TOLD HIM...

1:16:52.912 --> 1:16:54.697
WE'D DISTRIBUTE
HIS CLOTHING LINE

1:16:54.740 --> 1:16:57.090
UNDER GUCCI
AND HE COMMITTED TO A DEAL.

1:17:02.400 --> 1:17:04.968
MAURIZIO, THOSE DESIGNS
WON'T SEE THE LIGHT OF DAY.

1:17:05.011 --> 1:17:06.709
WE NEED PAOLO ON OUR SIDE.

1:17:07.710 --> 1:17:09.276
WHAT GAME ARE YOU PLAYING?

1:17:15.674 --> 1:17:17.458
I'M LOOKING OUT
FOR OUR BEST INTERESTS.

1:17:17.502 --> 1:17:18.590
IS THAT A GAME?

1:17:18.634 --> 1:17:20.853
[RAIN PATTERING]

1:17:25.075 --> 1:17:26.511
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1:17:33.779 --> 1:17:34.911
[BEEPS]

1:17:34.954 --> 1:17:35.738
[PAOLO EXCLAIMS]

1:17:38.436 --> 1:17:39.916
MAU, MAU!

1:17:39.959 --> 1:17:41.352
THANK YOU FOR COMING.

1:17:44.181 --> 1:17:45.922
YOU THOUGHT I LOST MY TOUCH.

1:17:45.965 --> 1:17:48.446
NO, NOT YET.

1:17:48.489 --> 1:17:49.969
[MAURIZIO] CIAO, PAOLO.

1:17:50.013 --> 1:17:51.014
YOU SOUNDED URGENT,
SO I CAME RIGHT AWAY.

1:17:51.057 --> 1:17:51.667
VERY WELL.

1:18:04.244 --> 1:18:09.772
I GOT THESE FROM THREE
OF HIS EX "SECRETARIES."

1:18:09.815 --> 1:18:12.600
HE'S NOT EXACTLY
A FAVORITE AMONG THE EX'S.

1:18:12.644 --> 1:18:15.342
IN FACT,
THEY ALL HATE HIS GUTS.

1:18:19.303 --> 1:18:25.352
GUCCI IS A VERY BLACK HOLE
OF UNDECLARED INCOME.

1:18:26.179 --> 1:18:28.355
PAOLO, THIS IS FRAUD...

1:18:28.399 --> 1:18:30.618
ON A GLOBAL SCALE.

1:18:30.662 --> 1:18:33.534
IN ITALY TAXES ARE OKAY,
BUT IN AMERICA...

1:18:34.405 --> 1:18:35.841
IT IS VERY DIFFERENT.

1:18:37.060 --> 1:18:39.540
WE SHOULD KEEP THIS
TO OURSELVES.

1:18:39.584 --> 1:18:42.674
[SPUTTERS] BUT WE CAN USE IT...

1:18:42.718 --> 1:18:46.069
AS LEVERAGE
TO PERSUADE HIM A BIT.

1:18:46.983 --> 1:18:48.549
AND WITH YOU...

1:18:49.159 --> 1:18:50.638
ON MY SIDE...

1:18:50.682 --> 1:18:53.380
WE HAVE THE MAJORITY WE NEED

1:18:53.424 --> 1:18:55.426
FOR YOU TO BECOME YOUR OWN MAN.

1:18:55.469 --> 1:18:59.386
AND HE WON'T GET INTO
ANY REAL TROUBLE, RIGHT?

1:18:59.430 --> 1:19:02.433
NO. [SPUTTERS] AT THIS POINT...

1:19:02.476 --> 1:19:05.175
WORST CASE SCENARIO,
HE PAYS HIS TAXES.

1:19:05.218 --> 1:19:06.872
THEY SLAP HIS WRISTS.

1:19:06.916 --> 1:19:08.265
HAPPENS ALL THE TIME.

1:19:09.832 --> 1:19:11.616
BUT MORE IMPORTANTLY,
HE WOULD SEE YOU.

1:19:13.661 --> 1:19:14.793
HE WOULD SEE YOU.

1:19:16.490 --> 1:19:17.491
[SIGHS]

1:19:18.492 --> 1:19:20.103
I COULD FINALLY SOAR...

1:19:21.931 --> 1:19:23.628
[EXHALES] LIKE A PIGEON.

1:19:27.110 --> 1:19:28.764
[PAOLO] I'M TIRED OF BEING
HELD BACK.

1:19:30.722 --> 1:19:33.029
FATHER, I'M TIRED
OF BEING HELD BACK.

1:19:33.072 --> 1:19:34.813
I'M SERIOUS.

1:19:36.293 --> 1:19:37.642
I'M SERIOUS.

1:19:37.685 --> 1:19:39.426
I'M TIRED OF BEING HELD BACK.

1:19:40.558 --> 1:19:41.777
I WANT FREEDOM.

1:19:42.299 --> 1:19:43.822
I'M SERIOUS.

1:19:43.866 --> 1:19:44.997
NO, I'M SERIOUS.

1:19:48.740 --> 1:19:49.828
HELLO?

1:19:50.873 --> 1:19:52.613
HELLO?

1:19:52.657 --> 1:19:53.876
-YEAH. THE--
-[PAOLO] HELLO,
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

1:19:53.919 --> 1:19:55.529
NO, IT'S A TERRIBLE LINE,
AND I--

1:19:55.573 --> 1:19:57.096
[PAOLO] CAN YOU HEAR ME NOW?

1:19:57.140 --> 1:20:00.926
-I CAN CALL YOU BACK.
-NO, NO. IT'S MIDNIGHT.

1:20:02.362 --> 1:20:04.277
IT'S LATE HERE. JUST TELL ME
WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND.

1:20:04.321 --> 1:20:05.235
WHAT HAPPENED?

1:20:05.278 --> 1:20:06.497
I, UH...

1:20:06.540 --> 1:20:08.716
I WANT MY FREEDOM.

1:20:09.935 --> 1:20:12.677
I'M TIRED OF BEING HELD BACK.

1:20:13.330 --> 1:20:14.374
I'M SERIOUS.

1:20:15.158 --> 1:20:16.637
[ALDO] FREEDOM?

1:20:16.681 --> 1:20:20.380
UH... PAOLO,
PLEASE JUST WAIT TILL TOMORROW.

1:20:20.424 --> 1:20:22.295
I'LL TALK TO YOU ABOUT IT
TOMORROW, ALL RIGHT?
I'M BUSY HERE.

1:20:22.339 --> 1:20:25.472
I HAVE YOUR TAX FILINGS.

1:20:26.909 --> 1:20:29.520
TAXES? WHAT ARE
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

1:20:29.563 --> 1:20:32.784
-THAT'S IT, PAOLO.
-I DON'T WANT TO
EXPOSE YOU, FATHER.

1:20:32.828 --> 1:20:34.873
I'LL TALK TO YOU TOMORROW.
GO TO BED.

1:20:34.917 --> 1:20:36.875
-YOU NEED TO GO TO BED,
PAOLO. ALL RIGHT?
-I, UH...

1:20:36.919 --> 1:20:38.529
["I'VE GOT YOUR NUMBER"
PLAYING]

1:20:49.540 --> 1:20:51.498
HI, ADRIANA. HOW ARE YOU?

1:20:51.542 --> 1:20:52.543
[ADRIANA] HI.

1:21:04.207 --> 1:21:05.077
AL.

1:21:06.035 --> 1:21:06.818
WHAT?

1:21:11.823 --> 1:21:12.737
WHAT?

1:21:21.659 --> 1:21:23.139
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

1:21:23.182 --> 1:21:27.752
CRIMINAL TAX EVASION
SOUNDS PRETTY SERIOUS.

1:21:27.795 --> 1:21:29.797
WHAT IF THEY DIG DEEPER?

1:21:29.841 --> 1:21:32.322
WHAT IF THEY FIND
EVEN MORE DIRT?

1:21:32.365 --> 1:21:34.715
MY FATHER, HE'S 70.

1:21:34.759 --> 1:21:36.935
HE'S NO SPRING CHICKEN.

1:21:36.979 --> 1:21:40.156
WE WERE JUST SUPPOSED
TO SPOOK HIM.

1:21:40.199 --> 1:21:41.157
[GROANS]

1:21:44.160 --> 1:21:47.990
DO YOU THINK HE'LL KNOW
IT WAS US?

1:21:48.033 --> 1:21:50.688
[MAURIZIO] PAOLO, NO, NO, NO.
HE'LL BE FINE.

1:21:50.731 --> 1:21:52.864
I'M SENDING A DRAFT
OF YOUR CONTRACT NEXT WEEK

1:21:52.908 --> 1:21:55.432
AND WE'LL GO INTO PRODUCTION
ON YOUR LINE SOON AFTER.

1:21:55.998 --> 1:21:57.608
[PAOLO] MY LINE?

1:21:57.651 --> 1:21:59.262
HOW CAN I THINK ABOUT MY LINE

1:21:59.305 --> 1:22:01.786
WHEN MY FATHER COULD BE
DROPPING THE SOAP?

1:22:03.048 --> 1:22:04.397
[SIGHS]

1:22:05.442 --> 1:22:07.444
PAOLO, ISN'T THIS
WHAT YOU WANTED?

1:22:10.926 --> 1:22:12.884
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1:22:12.928 --> 1:22:15.060
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

1:22:31.120 --> 1:22:32.251
PAOLO...

1:22:34.036 --> 1:22:36.255
HOW COULD YOU DO THIS TO ME?

1:22:36.864 --> 1:22:38.692
[GAVEL BANGING]

1:22:38.736 --> 1:22:40.520
MR. ALDO GUCCI.

1:22:44.046 --> 1:22:46.091
THIS COURT FINDS YOU GUILTY

1:22:46.135 --> 1:22:49.094
OF FIVE COUNTS OF FAILURE
TO FILE ACCURATE TAX RETURNS,

1:22:49.138 --> 1:22:52.271
ONE COUNT OF FAILURE
TO FILE A REPORT OF
A FOREIGN BANK ACCOUNT,

1:22:52.315 --> 1:22:54.317
AND TWO COUNTS OF BANK FRAUD.

1:22:54.360 --> 1:22:56.710
I HEREBY SENTENCE YOU
TO A YEAR AND A DAY

1:22:56.754 --> 1:22:58.321
IN A STATE PENITENTIARY.

1:22:58.364 --> 1:23:00.062
COURT WILL STAND ADJOURNED.

1:23:00.105 --> 1:23:01.324
[GAVEL POUNDS]

1:23:01.367 --> 1:23:03.456
[WOMAN SINGING OPERA]

1:23:33.356 --> 1:23:35.445
GOOD EVENING.
ARE YOU PAOLO GUCCI?

1:23:36.098 --> 1:23:37.316
THE ONE AND ONLY.

1:23:39.101 --> 1:23:40.885
ANOTHER PARKING TICKET?

1:23:45.020 --> 1:23:47.979
"CEASE AND DESIST"?

1:23:48.023 --> 1:23:52.027
WELL, YOU'VE BROKEN CERTAIN
EXCLUSIVE RIGHTS GRANTED
TO THE COPYRIGHT HOLDER

1:23:52.070 --> 1:23:56.901
SUCH AS THE RIGHT TO REPRODUCE,
DISTRIBUTE, DISPLAY OR PERFORM
A PROTECTED WORK.

1:23:58.424 --> 1:24:00.165
COPYRIGHT HOLDER?

1:24:00.948 --> 1:24:02.994
I AM THE COPYRIGHT.

1:24:03.038 --> 1:24:04.387
I AM SORRY.

1:24:04.430 --> 1:24:05.997
-DO SOMETHING.
-BUT IT'S GUCCI S.P.A.

1:24:10.784 --> 1:24:12.960
OH.

1:24:13.004 --> 1:24:19.315
[WOMAN SINGING OPERA]

1:24:24.972 --> 1:24:27.671
PLEASE, THE SHOW IS OVER.
THANK YOU.

1:24:27.714 --> 1:24:29.064
TOWARDS THE EXIT, PLEASE.

1:24:31.849 --> 1:24:33.590
WE HAVE TO GO,
PLEASE, EVERYONE.

1:24:35.244 --> 1:24:37.681
GET DOWN FROM THE CATWALK.
KEEP MOVING, PLEASE.

1:24:37.724 --> 1:24:38.551
THE SHOW IS OVER.

1:24:43.382 --> 1:24:44.557
TOWARDS THE EXIT.

1:24:57.353 --> 1:24:58.745
[STOPS SINGING]

1:25:13.891 --> 1:25:17.982
[CAR HONKS]

1:25:25.729 --> 1:25:26.469
[MAURIZIO] PAOLO.

1:25:30.255 --> 1:25:31.126
WHY?

1:25:32.214 --> 1:25:34.172
WHY?

1:25:34.216 --> 1:25:36.392
WHY DID YOU DO IT?

1:25:36.435 --> 1:25:38.872
-DO WHAT?
-WHAT HAPPENED?

1:25:38.916 --> 1:25:43.790
[PAOLO] DON'T EVEN LOOK AT ME,
YOU LYING SACK OF POTATOES.

1:25:43.834 --> 1:25:45.618
-SHUT YOUR FUCKING MOUTH.
-PAOLO.

1:25:45.662 --> 1:25:47.098
-WE ARE OUTSIDE THE CHURCH.
-PAOLO!

1:25:47.142 --> 1:25:48.273
-YOU SHUT YOUR FUCKING MOUTH.
-YOU SHUT YOUR MOUTH.

1:25:48.317 --> 1:25:49.840
THINK ABOUT ALESSANDRA.

1:25:49.883 --> 1:25:51.711
[PATRIZIA] GET HER IN THE CAR.

1:25:51.755 --> 1:25:53.670
-PUT ALESSANDRA IN THE CAR.
-PAOLO, WHAT'S WRONG?

1:25:53.713 --> 1:25:55.367
YOU...

1:25:55.411 --> 1:25:57.326
-AND YOU!
-OKAY. OKAY!

1:25:57.369 --> 1:26:01.025
YOU RIPPED MY HEART OUT,
LET IT DIE IN THE STREET.

1:26:01.068 --> 1:26:03.462
OH, MY GOD. MY WIFE...

1:26:03.506 --> 1:26:07.292
MY WIFE HAD TO SING
TILL HER VOICE WAS HOARSE...

1:26:07.336 --> 1:26:10.165
WHILE WE FIGURED OUT
WHAT THE FUCK WAS GOING ON.

1:26:12.254 --> 1:26:16.519
WHY DID YOU REPORT ME
FOR COPYRIGHT BREACH?

1:26:16.562 --> 1:26:18.782
GUCCI IS MY NAME TOO.

1:26:18.825 --> 1:26:21.828
YOU ABUSED THE GUCCI NAME.

1:26:21.872 --> 1:26:23.308
NO, NO.

1:26:23.352 --> 1:26:26.268
-AND STARTED A TRADE WAR.
-NO. I... NO.

1:26:26.311 --> 1:26:29.706
I DIDN'T. I SWEAR I DIDN'T,
OKAY?

1:26:29.749 --> 1:26:34.101
IT'S MY NAME.
IT'S NOT EVEN
YOUR REAL NAME, OKAY?

1:26:37.496 --> 1:26:39.281
MAU...

1:26:39.324 --> 1:26:43.067
MAU, IT'S ME, PAOLO.

1:26:43.763 --> 1:26:45.548
HOW COULD YOU?

1:26:47.724 --> 1:26:49.987
BUT WE'RE A FAMILY. HUH?

1:26:56.123 --> 1:26:58.648
WHAT ABOUT OUR FAMILY BUSINESS?

1:27:01.781 --> 1:27:02.782
YOU'RE RIGHT.

1:27:04.480 --> 1:27:05.655
-YOU'RE RIGHT.
-NO.

1:27:05.698 --> 1:27:07.091
WE ARE A FAMILY BUSINESS.

1:27:08.614 --> 1:27:10.268
YOU'RE RIGHT AND I DON'T
WANT TO HURT YOU.

1:27:10.312 --> 1:27:11.661
I WANT TO DO RIGHT BY YOU.

1:27:13.140 --> 1:27:15.839
BUT, PAOLO, WE HAVE
A PROPOSITION FOR YOU.

1:27:15.882 --> 1:27:17.449
IT'S THE ONLY WAY.

1:27:19.930 --> 1:27:20.887
[SCOFFS]

1:27:22.672 --> 1:27:23.673
SORRY.

1:27:27.285 --> 1:27:31.594
WE WANT TO BUY
YOUR SHARES OF GUCCI.

1:27:33.335 --> 1:27:34.727
[CHUCKLING]

1:27:38.253 --> 1:27:41.168
YOU GOT SOME COURAGE,
YOU KNOW THAT?

1:27:44.781 --> 1:27:50.526
AND SHE HAS BIGGER
MANGOES THAN YOU.

1:27:57.750 --> 1:28:01.363
YOU'RE A CHARACTER,
YOU KNOW THAT?

1:28:01.406 --> 1:28:04.409
MY QUIET LAWYER COUSIN.

1:28:04.453 --> 1:28:07.934
-OKAY. OKAY.
-THE TINY LITTLE MOUSE
IS A CHARACTER.

1:28:07.978 --> 1:28:09.806
-HEY, WATCH OUT.
-WHO KNEW?

1:28:12.069 --> 1:28:13.244
PAOLO, WE BOTH KNOW
IT'S FOR THE BEST.

1:28:13.766 --> 1:28:14.550
BOOF.

1:28:18.205 --> 1:28:23.950
NEVER CONFUSE SHIT
WITH CIOCCOLATO.

1:28:23.994 --> 1:28:26.779
THEY MAY LOOK THE SAME...

1:28:26.823 --> 1:28:28.651
BUT THE TASTE?

1:28:28.694 --> 1:28:30.174
VERY DIFFERENT.

1:28:30.217 --> 1:28:34.657
TRUST ME, I KNOW.

1:28:34.700 --> 1:28:40.184
I'D RATHER SEE GUCCI BURN
THAN TO HAND IT OVER
TO YOU TWO BASTARDS.

1:28:42.708 --> 1:28:43.274
CIAO.

1:28:46.756 --> 1:28:48.192
COME ON, LET'S GO.

1:28:50.455 --> 1:28:51.195
[PAOLO GROANS]

1:28:52.414 --> 1:28:53.632
PAOLO...

1:28:53.676 --> 1:28:55.765
LET'S GO, MAURIZIO. COME ON.

1:29:02.119 --> 1:29:03.860
HOW DO YOU KNOW ALL THIS?

1:29:03.903 --> 1:29:05.209
MAURIZIO, COULD YOU...

1:29:11.868 --> 1:29:12.999
THERE'S THE POLICE.

1:29:14.523 --> 1:29:15.654
THE POLICE ARE HERE?

1:29:15.698 --> 1:29:17.221
YEAH. FINANCIAL POLICE.

1:29:20.485 --> 1:29:22.008
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

1:29:36.762 --> 1:29:38.198
-GO.
-GO UPSTAIRS.

1:29:38.242 --> 1:29:39.678
-GATHER WITH ME.
-CHECK EVERYWHERE.

1:29:39.722 --> 1:29:40.462
COME ON.

1:29:41.898 --> 1:29:42.942
PLEASE. IN THERE.

1:29:53.692 --> 1:29:54.301
[EXHALES]

1:30:06.183 --> 1:30:08.054
-CAN I HELP YOU?
-NO.

1:30:13.930 --> 1:30:15.279
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

1:30:22.155 --> 1:30:23.156
SIGNORE!

1:30:23.722 --> 1:30:24.854
CAN I HELP YOU?

1:30:24.897 --> 1:30:26.943
OF COURSE, MADAM.

1:30:26.986 --> 1:30:28.858
PATRIZIA GUCCI.

1:30:28.901 --> 1:30:31.295
ALBERTO DE RENZI.
MAN IN CHARGE OF THE OPERATION.

1:30:32.427 --> 1:30:33.689
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

1:30:33.732 --> 1:30:36.169
[ALBERTO] NO, THANK YOU.
WE DON'T DRINK.

1:30:36.213 --> 1:30:38.476
-JOHNNIE WALKER?
SPLASH OF WATER?
-NEITHER, THANK YOU.

1:30:53.186 --> 1:30:54.405
[GUARD] PASSPORT PLEASE.

1:30:59.758 --> 1:31:00.890
AND OPEN YOUR VISOR.

1:31:18.255 --> 1:31:19.125
THANK YOU.

1:31:44.629 --> 1:31:46.936
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

1:31:46.979 --> 1:31:48.851
THANK YOU, ROBERTO.

1:31:48.894 --> 1:31:51.027
[PATRIZIA]
YOU'RE NOT LISTENING TO ME.

1:31:51.070 --> 1:31:53.029
I'M HERE TO HELP YOU.

1:31:53.072 --> 1:31:53.769
THANK YOU, SIGNORAGUCCI.

1:31:55.031 --> 1:31:57.947
WE JUST NEED TO PERFORM
A FEW MORE ANALYSES.

1:31:57.990 --> 1:32:00.384
[PATRIZIA] PLEASE,
LET ME HELP YOU.

1:32:00.427 --> 1:32:04.083
I'M VERY RESOURCEFUL.
LET'S DISCUSS.

1:32:04.127 --> 1:32:05.737
WE HAVE NOTHING MORE
TO SAY AT THIS MOMENT.

1:32:05.781 --> 1:32:07.347
THANK YOU. THANK YOU.

1:32:07.391 --> 1:32:08.653
THANK YOU.

1:32:08.697 --> 1:32:11.177
PATRIZIA, PLEASE. PLEASE.

1:32:11.221 --> 1:32:12.962
-GOODBYE, SIGNORAGUCCI.
-DOMENICO, PLEASE.

1:32:14.616 --> 1:32:16.574
[GASPING]

1:32:16.618 --> 1:32:18.184
IT TOOK YOU
FUCKING LONG ENOUGH.

1:32:18.228 --> 1:32:19.969
MAURIZIO CALLED
FROM ST. MORITZ...

1:32:20.012 --> 1:32:22.058
AND HE SAID YOU CAN JOIN HIM
THERE WHENEVER YOU WANT.

1:32:28.325 --> 1:32:30.066
[SOBBING] THEY TOOK
MY DAUGHTER'S SHOES.

1:32:39.118 --> 1:32:41.120
[BANGING ON TABLE]

1:32:41.164 --> 1:32:43.253
WHAT'S THIS ABOUT
A FORGED SIGNATURE?

1:32:44.254 --> 1:32:45.298
EH?

1:32:48.563 --> 1:32:50.173
WHAT FORGED SIGNATURE?

1:32:50.216 --> 1:32:51.870
YOU KNOW NOTHING ABOUT IT?

1:32:54.917 --> 1:32:55.961
GET THEM OUT.

1:32:56.005 --> 1:32:57.441
-YEAH.
-YEAH.

1:33:02.054 --> 1:33:03.012
PAOLO.

1:33:05.275 --> 1:33:06.276
PAOLO.

1:33:07.669 --> 1:33:09.018
MUST BE PAOLO.

1:33:09.061 --> 1:33:10.802
YEAH. I TOLD YOU
HE WAS FUCKING TROUBLE.

1:33:10.846 --> 1:33:11.498
IDIOT.

1:34:13.125 --> 1:34:14.518
MAURIZIO?

1:34:20.089 --> 1:34:21.612
PAOLA.

1:34:21.656 --> 1:34:23.527
-I KNEW IT WAS YOU.
-OH, WOW!

1:34:23.962 --> 1:34:24.789
PAOLA.

1:34:25.442 --> 1:34:26.617
YOU LOOK EXACTLY THE SAME.

1:34:27.357 --> 1:34:28.750
SO DO YOU.

1:34:28.793 --> 1:34:30.316
UNTIL THEN,
YOU'RE COMING WITH US.

1:34:30.360 --> 1:34:31.709
-[MAURIZIO] I AM NOT GOING.
-BECAUSE YOU SAID YOU WERE.

1:34:31.753 --> 1:34:32.797
NO. I ALWAYS WANTED TO COME.

1:34:32.841 --> 1:34:33.624
YOU SAID YOU WOULD.

1:34:35.191 --> 1:34:36.453
[MAN] MAURIZIO, MAURIZIO!

1:34:46.376 --> 1:34:47.377
[MAURIZIO] HEY...

1:34:49.858 --> 1:34:51.598
[CHUCKLING]

1:34:51.642 --> 1:34:53.122
[PATRIZIA] HOPE
I'M NOT INTERRUPTING.

1:34:53.165 --> 1:34:54.645
NO, OF COURSE NOT.
YOU'RE NOT INTERRUPTING.

1:34:56.473 --> 1:34:58.344
I SEE YOU'VE PUT UP THE TREE.

1:34:58.388 --> 1:34:59.998
[MAURIZIO] YES. YES.

1:35:00.042 --> 1:35:02.261
EVERYBODY, THIS IS PATRIZIA.

1:35:03.741 --> 1:35:06.048
-HEY, PATRIZIA.
-AND THIS IS ALESSANDRA.

1:35:07.484 --> 1:35:10.443
-HELLO.
-FRANCO AND GIANNI,
YOU KNOW, OF COURSE.

1:35:10.487 --> 1:35:12.141
THIS IS MY FRIEND PAOLA...

1:35:12.184 --> 1:35:14.796
AND THESE ARE
ALL OF HER SLAVES.

1:35:14.839 --> 1:35:16.058
[ALL CHUCKLING]

1:35:16.101 --> 1:35:16.885
ALESSANDRA.

1:35:21.193 --> 1:35:22.151
OH, SORRY.

1:35:24.980 --> 1:35:27.460
WHAT DO YOU THINK
OF THE MACAROONS?

1:35:27.504 --> 1:35:30.594
THIS HAZELNUT ONE
IS TO DIE FOR.

1:35:30.637 --> 1:35:34.206
YEAH. WHERE DID YOU GET 'EM?

1:35:34.250 --> 1:35:38.036
THERE IS THIS CHARMING
LITTLE PLACE BY
NOTRE-DAME-DE-LORETTE IN PARIS.

1:35:38.080 --> 1:35:42.171
"DE-LORETTE."
NOTRE-DAME-DE-LORETTE.

1:35:42.214 --> 1:35:42.954
-RIGHT.
-DE-LORETTE.

1:35:44.913 --> 1:35:47.132
MAURIZIO AND I STAYED THERE
FIVE YEARS AGO.

1:35:48.090 --> 1:35:50.657
WE HAD THE MOST AMAZING TIME.

1:35:50.701 --> 1:35:54.052
I BEGGED MAURIZIO
TO TAKE ME THERE
FOR MY 25TH BIRTHDAY.

1:35:54.096 --> 1:35:56.968
AND OF COURSE, HE OBLIGED.

1:35:58.709 --> 1:36:01.233
AS SOON AS WE LANDED,
WE WENT TO
THE JULES VERNE RESTAURANT...

1:36:01.277 --> 1:36:02.887
IN THE EIFFEL TOWER.

1:36:02.931 --> 1:36:04.715
IT'S AT THE TOP.

1:36:04.759 --> 1:36:06.456
NO, NO, NO.
IT'S ON THE SECOND FLOOR.

1:36:09.111 --> 1:36:10.634
IT WAS MAGNIFICENT.

1:36:11.766 --> 1:36:13.768
LATER WE WENT TO THE LOUVRE.

1:36:13.811 --> 1:36:16.074
I'D ALWAYS DREAMT
OF SEEING THE LOUVRE.

1:36:16.118 --> 1:36:18.816
WE ARRANGED
FOR A PRIVATE TOUR.
THANK GOD.

1:36:18.860 --> 1:36:21.471
IMAGINE ALL THOSE CROWDS.
I COULDN'T DO IT.

1:36:21.514 --> 1:36:24.256
THEY JUST WANT TO KNOW
WHERE YOU GOT
THE MACAROONS, SWEETIE.

1:36:24.300 --> 1:36:26.128
I'M TELLING THEM.

1:36:26.171 --> 1:36:27.999
YEAH, YOU'RE FILLING THE STORY
FULL OF UNNECESSARY DETAILS.

1:36:29.958 --> 1:36:31.655
[PATRIZIA] I DON'T THINK
OUR GUESTS MIND.

1:36:31.698 --> 1:36:33.700
THEY WOULDN'T SAY IF THEY DID.

1:36:35.746 --> 1:36:37.661
YOU'RE AN UNNECESSARY DETAIL.

1:36:39.445 --> 1:36:40.838
[LAUGHING]

1:36:46.061 --> 1:36:48.019
WHAT I AM TRYING
TO TELL YOU IS...

1:36:48.063 --> 1:36:52.458
DE SOLE IS THE ONLY PERSON
WHO SAW
THE UNSIGNED CERTIFICATES.

1:36:52.502 --> 1:36:55.679
HE WORKED FOR MY FATHER
FOR TEN YEARS AND
HE NEVER QUESTIONED HIM.

1:36:56.549 --> 1:36:57.681
I TRUST HIM.

1:36:59.161 --> 1:37:00.684
HE'S NOT THE PROBLEM.

1:37:02.599 --> 1:37:04.296
I HEARD THE WAY YOU SPOKE
TO ME AT LUNCH.

1:37:04.340 --> 1:37:05.863
HE'S NOT THE PROBLEM?

1:37:05.907 --> 1:37:07.169
[MAURIZIO] I WAS TIRED.

1:37:09.824 --> 1:37:13.610
NEXT TIME,
DON'T EMBARRASS ME
IN FRONT OF THOSE PEOPLE.

1:37:13.653 --> 1:37:15.873
THOSE PEOPLE
ARE FRIENDS OF MINE.

1:37:15.917 --> 1:37:18.354
I'VE KNOWN MOST OF THEM
LONGER THAN YOU.

1:37:19.529 --> 1:37:22.358
HE IS THE PROBLEM. SAY IT!

1:37:22.401 --> 1:37:25.796
PATRIZIA, I WAS TIRED.
I'M TIRED.

1:37:25.840 --> 1:37:28.451
THEN WAKE YOURSELF UP
AND SAY IT.

1:37:28.494 --> 1:37:30.018
[MAURIZIO] OKAY.

1:37:30.061 --> 1:37:33.108
WHEN YOU MAKE ME
SNEAK AROUND MY OWN FAMILY.

1:37:33.151 --> 1:37:35.458
WHEN YOU SET FATHER AND SON
AGAINST EACH OTHER...

1:37:35.501 --> 1:37:37.416
AND ME AGAINST PAOLO.

1:37:37.460 --> 1:37:40.811
WHEN YOU SECOND-GUESS A PERSON
LIKE DOMENICO DE SOLE...

1:37:40.855 --> 1:37:43.858
THE ONLY PERSON
MY FATHER TRUSTED.

1:37:43.901 --> 1:37:46.991
THESE THINGS HAVE
AN EFFECT ON THE ENVIRONMENT
I OPERATE IN. ON ME.

1:37:48.645 --> 1:37:50.429
ACTIONS HAVE CONSEQUENCES.

1:37:50.473 --> 1:37:53.345
[PATRIZIA] I DID THAT FOR YOU.
I WAS BEING CONSTRUCTIVE.

1:37:53.389 --> 1:37:56.174
I'M NOT GONNA APOLOGIZE
FOR THAT. NO THANKS.

1:37:58.176 --> 1:38:01.832
MY UNCLE IS IN PRISON
AND MY COUSIN THINKS
I'M SCUM.

1:38:01.876 --> 1:38:03.921
AND YOU THINK
THAT'S CONSTRUCTIVE?

1:38:03.965 --> 1:38:06.141
DON'T PIN GUCCI'S PROBLEMS
ON ME, OKAY?

1:38:06.184 --> 1:38:08.230
I'M JUST HERE MOPPING UP
YOUR FUCKING MESS.

1:38:08.273 --> 1:38:09.753
I NEVER ASKED FOR YOUR HELP.

1:38:21.852 --> 1:38:23.549
MAURIZIO...

1:38:23.593 --> 1:38:25.421
WE'RE ONLY STRONGER TOGETHER.

1:38:26.988 --> 1:38:27.858
[SIGHS]

1:38:30.208 --> 1:38:32.863
THE ONLY THING
I NEED FROM YOU...

1:38:32.907 --> 1:38:35.910
IS TO STAY AWAY FROM GUCCI
BEFORE YOU CAUSE
ANY MORE DAMAGE.

1:38:37.781 --> 1:38:40.523
I CAN HANDLE IT BY MYSELF.

1:38:40.566 --> 1:38:41.828
IS THAT CLEAR?

1:38:46.007 --> 1:38:48.923
TRUTHFULLY, I'M ONLY
GETTING INVOLVED...

1:38:48.966 --> 1:38:52.970
BECAUSE YOU ARE
AN INCOMPETENT,
LITTLE BABY IDIOT.

1:38:53.014 --> 1:38:55.799
YOU'RE A FUCKING
WEAK LITTLE BRAT.

1:38:55.842 --> 1:38:58.454
YOU REALLY ARE ONLY
ONE HALF OF GUCCI.

1:38:58.497 --> 1:38:59.803
THE SHIT HALF.

1:39:04.547 --> 1:39:06.201
AND YOU WANT A REAL MAN?

1:39:06.244 --> 1:39:07.419
HERE.

1:39:07.463 --> 1:39:08.812
MAYBE YOU'LL GROW A LITTLE.

1:39:25.089 --> 1:39:27.483
-[GAME BEEPING]
-[MAURIZIO] RED, GREEN,
RED, GREEN. RED.

1:39:27.526 --> 1:39:29.441
-GREEN.
-[MAURIZIO] RED.

1:39:29.485 --> 1:39:31.661
-[ALESSANDRA] GREEN.
-[MAURIZIO]
VERY GOOD, ALESSANDRA.

1:39:31.704 --> 1:39:33.141
-GREEN, RED.
-[ALESSANDRA] GREEN.

1:39:33.184 --> 1:39:34.664
-[MAURIZIO] GREEN, RED.
-[ALESSANDRA] GREEN.

1:39:34.707 --> 1:39:36.231
-I THINK THAT'S IT.
-[ALESSANDRA] GREEN.

1:39:36.274 --> 1:39:38.015
[MAURIZIO] RED, GREEN,
RED, GREEN, RED, BLUE.

1:39:38.059 --> 1:39:41.062
[BOTH] RED, GREEN. RED, GREEN.

1:39:41.105 --> 1:39:43.281
RED, BLUE.

1:39:43.325 --> 1:39:46.545
[MAURIZIO] RED, GREEN,
RED, GREEN, RED, BLUE.
YELLOW. OKAY.

1:39:46.589 --> 1:39:50.854
-RED. GREEN. RED. GREEN. RED.
-RED. GREEN. RED. GREEN.

1:39:50.897 --> 1:39:52.334
-BLUE. YELLOW.
-BLUE. YELLOW.

1:39:54.075 --> 1:39:56.033
-YOU'RE VERY...
-THE WINNER.

1:39:56.077 --> 1:39:57.513
[CHUCKLING]

1:39:57.556 --> 1:39:58.862
THE WINNER GETS A PRESENT.

1:40:00.951 --> 1:40:03.084
FOR ALESSANDRA.

1:40:03.127 --> 1:40:05.260
[ALESSANDRA]
THANK YOU, MOMMY.

1:40:05.303 --> 1:40:07.001
WE'LL PLAY LATER.

1:40:13.529 --> 1:40:14.704
WHO IS THAT?

1:40:15.792 --> 1:40:16.923
TURN IT AROUND.

1:40:18.142 --> 1:40:19.926
WHO IS THAT...

1:40:19.970 --> 1:40:21.232
WHO IS HIDING IN THERE?

1:40:24.105 --> 1:40:25.541
I LOVE YOU.

1:40:25.584 --> 1:40:26.933
I LOVE YOU.

1:40:28.283 --> 1:40:30.372
-[SPEAKING ITALIAN]
-MERRY CHRISTMAS.

1:40:31.982 --> 1:40:33.157
DO YOU LIKE HIM?

1:40:34.811 --> 1:40:36.987
FOR DADDY, FROM ME.

1:40:43.646 --> 1:40:46.518
YOU CAN CHANGE THE STRAP
IF YOU DON'T LIKE THAT COLOR.

1:40:46.562 --> 1:40:47.911
OH, NO. IT'S FINE.

1:40:51.219 --> 1:40:52.002
OKAY.

1:40:53.569 --> 1:40:54.700
THANK YOU.

1:40:59.966 --> 1:41:02.708
FOR MOMMY, FROM DADDY.

1:41:03.753 --> 1:41:05.015
MMM...

1:41:05.059 --> 1:41:06.582
I NEVER KNOW WHAT TO GET YOU.

1:41:08.714 --> 1:41:10.194
I'M SURE IT'S PERFECT.

1:41:21.988 --> 1:41:23.773
A BLOOMINGDALE'S GIFT CARD.

1:41:25.427 --> 1:41:27.211
YEAH, NOW YOU CAN
GET WHAT YOU WANT.

1:41:29.692 --> 1:41:30.954
YOU KNOW I NEVER SHOP THERE.

1:41:33.261 --> 1:41:36.046
WELL, THERE IS A FIRST TIME
FOR EVERYTHING.

1:41:36.090 --> 1:41:37.961
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

1:41:57.502 --> 1:41:59.635
-PAOLA, DARLING.
-OH.

1:41:59.678 --> 1:42:01.767
LOVE THE ALL-WHITE OUTFIT.

1:42:01.811 --> 1:42:03.160
SO CHIC.

1:42:03.204 --> 1:42:05.641
I MADE SOME STRUDEL
FOR YOU AND M.

1:42:05.684 --> 1:42:07.860
IT'S THE ONLY THING
I KNOW HOW TO MAKE.

1:42:07.904 --> 1:42:11.255
I'M ON A DIET,
BUT I'M SURE MAURIZIO
WILL LOVE YOUR STRUDEL.

1:42:11.299 --> 1:42:12.082
OH.

1:42:14.128 --> 1:42:15.651
WOULD YOU LIKE A CIGARETTE?

1:42:15.694 --> 1:42:16.695
NO.

1:42:17.653 --> 1:42:19.176
[THANKING IN ITALIAN]

1:42:25.095 --> 1:42:26.966
YOU EVER STEAL ANYTHING, PAOLA?

1:42:27.489 --> 1:42:28.490
WHAT?

1:42:29.230 --> 1:42:30.883
FORGIVE ME.

1:42:30.927 --> 1:42:32.929
I AM TRYING TO TEACH
ALESSANDRA...

1:42:32.972 --> 1:42:35.192
THE IMPORTANCE OF
NOT TOUCHING OTHER PEOPLE'S
BELONGINGS.

1:42:44.158 --> 1:42:47.552
I DON'T CONSIDER MYSELF
A PARTICULARLY
ETHICAL PERSON...

1:42:47.596 --> 1:42:48.858
BUT I AM FAIR.

1:42:52.688 --> 1:42:54.864
WHAT I CANNOT
WRAP MY HEAD AROUND...

1:42:56.735 --> 1:42:59.695
IS PEOPLE WHO STEAL
JUST FOR EGO.

1:43:00.565 --> 1:43:02.263
OR THE PLEASURE OF IT.

1:43:03.829 --> 1:43:06.049
FOR PERSONAL SATISFACTION.

1:43:21.238 --> 1:43:23.066
I'LL HAVE MY MAID
DROP OFF THE STRUDEL.

1:43:27.201 --> 1:43:28.463
GOOD TO SEE YOU.

1:43:34.469 --> 1:43:35.078
[SCOFFS]

1:43:39.561 --> 1:43:42.085
[CLOCK CHIMING]

1:43:47.221 --> 1:43:48.178
[CLEARS THROAT]

1:43:51.312 --> 1:43:53.096
[PATRIZIA]
DO YOU LIKE MY HAIR?

1:44:03.628 --> 1:44:05.587
MAURIZIO,
DO YOU LIKE MY HAIR?

1:44:08.198 --> 1:44:10.069
OH, YES, VERY NICE.

1:44:10.113 --> 1:44:11.114
VERY CHIC.

1:44:12.855 --> 1:44:14.117
I WAS THINKING, TOMORROW...

1:44:40.448 --> 1:44:42.363
FRANCO IS COMING
TOMORROW AT NOON.

1:44:44.713 --> 1:44:46.192
WHY?

1:44:49.065 --> 1:44:51.328
TO TAKE YOU BOTH
BACK TO MILAN.

1:44:55.811 --> 1:44:57.508
CAN WE AT LEAST
TALK ABOUT IT?

1:45:05.951 --> 1:45:06.865
[SOBS]

1:45:14.090 --> 1:45:17.267
I'LL FIND THE RIGHT WORDS
TO SAY WHAT I WANT TO SAY
WHEN I'M READY.

1:45:20.096 --> 1:45:22.838
YOU REALLY, REALLY HURT ME.

1:45:34.719 --> 1:45:35.459
[DOOR CLOSES]

1:45:36.112 --> 1:45:37.287
PAOLO WON'T DO IT.

1:45:37.331 --> 1:45:39.681
HE'S TOO SCARED
OF HIS FATHER.

1:45:39.724 --> 1:45:41.160
[DOMENICO]
HE'S DROWNING IN DEBT.

1:45:41.204 --> 1:45:43.206
BUT WE CAN'T BUY HIM OUT.

1:45:43.249 --> 1:45:45.208
WE NEED A CASH PARTNER,
MAURIZIO.

1:45:45.861 --> 1:45:47.732
WHO DO YOU SUGGEST?

1:45:47.776 --> 1:45:49.865
INVESTCORP.

1:45:49.908 --> 1:45:54.130
IT'S OWNED BY NEMIR KIRDAR.
HE'S AN IRAQI POWERHOUSE.

1:45:54.173 --> 1:45:56.872
THEY LIKE HIGH-END
RETAIL INVESTMENTS.

1:45:56.915 --> 1:45:59.440
THEY BOUGHT TIFFANY'S IN '84
AND TURNED IT AROUND QUICK.

1:46:09.537 --> 1:46:10.842
MAURIZIO.

1:46:12.366 --> 1:46:14.846
[MAURIZIO]
PLANT THE SEED WITH HIM.
I'LL BE BACK SOON.

1:46:19.329 --> 1:46:20.461
[PATRIZIA]
SOMETHING'S DIFFERENT.

1:46:21.244 --> 1:46:22.724
MAURIZIO'S CHANGED.

1:46:22.767 --> 1:46:24.639
HE'S EXCESSIVE...

1:46:26.380 --> 1:46:27.468
AND CRAZY.

1:46:28.947 --> 1:46:30.427
AND THAT WOMAN...

1:46:32.255 --> 1:46:34.213
[GIUSEPPINA]
DON'T BE SCARED.

1:46:34.257 --> 1:46:38.174
HE'S NOTHING WITHOUT YOU.
HMM?

1:46:38.217 --> 1:46:43.048
MEN HAVE AN AWFUL PROBLEM
WITH THINKING THEY ARE
SMARTER THAN THEY ACTUALLY ARE.

1:46:43.092 --> 1:46:47.705
YOU MUSTN'T
LET THIS NEGATIVE ENERGY
EAT YOU UP.

1:46:47.749 --> 1:46:48.445
HUH?

1:46:49.881 --> 1:46:51.927
REMEMBER...

1:46:51.970 --> 1:46:54.277
YOU ARE UNSTOPPABLE, PATRIZIA.

1:46:54.973 --> 1:46:56.279
SAY IT.

1:46:57.106 --> 1:46:58.847
I'M UNSTOPPABLE.

1:47:02.981 --> 1:47:04.461
I'M UNSTOPPABLE.

1:47:06.942 --> 1:47:08.552
I AM ONLY 50% OF GUCCI.

1:47:08.596 --> 1:47:12.382
I'M HERE REPRESENTING
MY OWN INTERESTS.

1:47:12.426 --> 1:47:15.646
I WANT SOMEONE TO BRING
GUCCI TO THE FOREFRONT
OF TODAY'S FASHION.

1:47:18.040 --> 1:47:20.695
I WANT A PARTNER
WHO CAN BUY OUT
THE OTHER HALF OF GUCCI...

1:47:20.738 --> 1:47:23.567
THAT'S GIVING ME A HEADACHE.

1:47:23.611 --> 1:47:28.137
THE HALF
THAT'S PREVENTING GUCCI
FROM BEING GREAT.

1:47:28.180 --> 1:47:31.488
THE HALF THAT BELONGS TO
YOUR UNCLE AND YOUR COUSIN.

1:47:31.532 --> 1:47:33.708
INVESTCORP HAS
HAD GREAT SUCCESS
WITH TIFFANY.

1:47:33.751 --> 1:47:35.710
IT IS...
IT IS A RESURRECTION.

1:47:35.753 --> 1:47:38.277
TRUE. BUT TIFFANY ISN'T GUCCI.

1:47:38.321 --> 1:47:40.149
GUCCI IS A FAMILY BUSINESS.

1:47:40.192 --> 1:47:41.324
THAT MEANS FAMILY PROBLEMS.

1:47:43.065 --> 1:47:44.980
YEAH, WELL, I BROUGHT
SOMETHING FOR YOU.

1:48:01.779 --> 1:48:02.432
BURGUNDY.

1:48:03.651 --> 1:48:06.915
SIZE TEN U.S. WIDE, RIGHT?

1:48:06.958 --> 1:48:09.526
THIS MODEL IS PART
OF THE PERMANENT COLLECTION...

1:48:09.570 --> 1:48:11.354
AT THE METROPOLITAN MUSEUM
IN NEW YORK.

1:48:12.398 --> 1:48:14.270
YOU CAN'T BUY IT ANYWHERE.

1:48:16.838 --> 1:48:17.969
AND NOW IT IS YOURS.

1:48:26.891 --> 1:48:29.328
["HEART OF GLASS" PLAYING]

1:48:45.606 --> 1:48:47.390
YES, I...

1:48:47.433 --> 1:48:49.000
WELL, I...

1:48:49.044 --> 1:48:50.828
WELL, WHEN THEN?

1:48:52.830 --> 1:48:54.092
I'VE GOT TO WASH.

1:48:56.225 --> 1:49:00.185
IF YOU COULD
SMELL BETWEEN MY GROINS,
YOU'D UNDERSTAND.

1:49:03.058 --> 1:49:04.146
SI.

1:49:04.189 --> 1:49:05.190
NO, NOT...

1:49:06.061 --> 1:49:07.323
PAOLO.

1:49:25.907 --> 1:49:27.691
[CHUCKLING]

1:49:29.563 --> 1:49:30.433
COME ON.

1:49:30.955 --> 1:49:32.087
UH...

1:49:32.130 --> 1:49:34.089
I THINK IT'S, UH...

1:49:35.264 --> 1:49:36.874
NO, I KNOW.

1:49:36.918 --> 1:49:39.181
-I KNOW, IT'S...
-YOU KNOW WHAT?

1:49:39.224 --> 1:49:40.574
THERE'S NO CARS THERE.

1:49:40.617 --> 1:49:43.011
[PAOLO STUTTERS]
WELL, NO, NO, NO.

1:49:43.054 --> 1:49:45.840
IT'S OVER THERE.

1:49:45.883 --> 1:49:48.277
IT'S OVER HERE.
IT'S HERE, I KNOW.

1:49:48.320 --> 1:49:50.018
FUCK A DUCK, IT'S OVER HERE.

1:49:50.061 --> 1:49:51.628
WHAT KIND OF CAR IS IT?

1:49:51.672 --> 1:49:53.456
FIAT 600.

1:49:54.849 --> 1:49:55.937
-FIAT.
-AH...

1:49:56.938 --> 1:49:58.287
FIAT 600.

1:49:59.331 --> 1:50:01.116
PAOLO, IT'S HERE.

1:50:02.465 --> 1:50:03.248
BOOF.

1:50:08.993 --> 1:50:09.907
[GROANS SOFTLY]

1:50:12.997 --> 1:50:15.086
HERE. RIGHT HERE.

1:50:16.610 --> 1:50:17.523
[GROANS SOFTLY]

1:50:19.874 --> 1:50:20.744
BOOF.

1:50:22.354 --> 1:50:23.965
-[SIGHS]
-[KEYS CLINK]

1:50:26.097 --> 1:50:27.359
WELL...

1:50:28.796 --> 1:50:31.494
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU WOULD
END UP IN PRISON.

1:50:32.974 --> 1:50:35.367
-WHAT?
-I HATE MYSELF FOR IT.

1:50:35.411 --> 1:50:36.586
DON'T, PLEASE.

1:50:38.588 --> 1:50:41.069
WHAT DID YOU DO HERE?
WHAT IS THIS?

1:50:41.112 --> 1:50:43.549
WELL, I HAVE BEEN
A BIT STRESSED.

1:50:43.593 --> 1:50:44.594
NO, IT IS...

1:50:47.379 --> 1:50:50.774
-WE HAVE TO CLEAN THIS.
-WELL, MY LIFE HAS BEEN
HARD. REALLY HARD.

1:50:50.818 --> 1:50:52.994
-I HAVEN'T SHIT IN A WEEK.
-NO, IT'S FILTHY!

1:50:53.037 --> 1:50:55.997
AND THAT BITCH OF A WIFE
PROMISED TO HELP ME.

1:50:56.040 --> 1:50:58.956
HE SHOOK MY HAND WHILE
SHE KNIFED ME IN THE BACK.

1:50:59.000 --> 1:51:01.916
-OH, PAOLO.
-I'VE BEEN DROWNING
IN LEGAL FEES.

1:51:01.959 --> 1:51:04.092
IT'S BEEN
REALLY, REALLY BAD.

1:51:04.135 --> 1:51:05.746
-I KNOW.
-I COULDN'T EVEN MAKE LOVE.

1:51:05.789 --> 1:51:08.749
JENNY LEFT. AND AFTER THAT,
I WAS IN BED...

1:51:08.792 --> 1:51:11.142
-JENNY.
-...WITH A POUND
OF GELATO CIOCCOLATO...

1:51:11.186 --> 1:51:12.883
AND VERY DARK THOUGHTS.

1:51:12.927 --> 1:51:14.580
I AM BACK. I AM BACK.

1:51:14.624 --> 1:51:18.497
WE WILL START
WHERE WE LEFT OFF.

1:51:18.541 --> 1:51:19.542
OKAY?

1:51:20.674 --> 1:51:24.590
I ALSO GLAD
TO HAVE YOU BACK.

1:51:24.634 --> 1:51:27.332
WELL, IT'S GOOD
TO BE BACK TOO.

1:51:31.423 --> 1:51:33.338
WELL, LOOK AT THIS PLACE.

1:51:35.253 --> 1:51:36.820
IT LOOKS LIKE IT'S GIVEN UP.

1:51:38.996 --> 1:51:40.302
WHAT?

1:51:40.345 --> 1:51:41.564
-WELL...
-WHAT?

1:51:51.269 --> 1:51:52.009
[LIGHTER CLICKS]

1:51:55.621 --> 1:51:56.710
WHAT'S THAT?

1:51:58.799 --> 1:52:00.496
[PAOLO] A REALLY GOOD DEAL.

1:52:02.803 --> 1:52:03.804
WHAT DEAL?

1:52:04.848 --> 1:52:07.590
I MET WITH THEIR LAWYERS TOO.

1:52:09.548 --> 1:52:11.768
I COULDN'T SAY NO.
I NEEDED THE CASH.

1:52:11.812 --> 1:52:13.074
I MEAN LOOK AT THIS DUMP.

1:52:13.117 --> 1:52:16.033
I DON'T EVEN HAVE BASIC CABLE.

1:52:16.381 --> 1:52:17.469
NO.

1:52:21.343 --> 1:52:23.998
I SOLD MY SHARES
OF GUCCI TO THEM!

1:52:24.041 --> 1:52:25.956
[YELLS] NO!

1:52:26.391 --> 1:52:27.610
NO!

1:52:29.177 --> 1:52:31.005
NO! NO!

1:52:32.310 --> 1:52:33.485
[SIGHS]

1:52:36.488 --> 1:52:37.620
[SIGHS]

1:52:42.059 --> 1:52:44.018
I KNOW. I'M DONE.

1:52:44.061 --> 1:52:46.237
-NO. NO. NO.
-NO, I'M DONE. I'M DEAD.

1:52:46.281 --> 1:52:47.499
-I'M DEAD.
-NO.

1:52:47.543 --> 1:52:48.674
I'M DEAD!

1:52:49.023 --> 1:52:50.241
DEAD!

1:52:54.289 --> 1:52:55.638
COME. COME HERE.

1:53:01.122 --> 1:53:02.253
YOU'RE...

1:53:03.472 --> 1:53:04.734
AN IDIOT.

1:53:06.954 --> 1:53:10.435
BUT YOU'RE MY...
YOU'RE MY IDIOT.

1:53:10.479 --> 1:53:12.655
MAURIZIO, THESE MUST'VE
COST YOU A FORTUNE.

1:53:14.091 --> 1:53:15.571
ART HAS NO PRICE.

1:53:15.614 --> 1:53:17.355
I'M SCARED TO TOUCH ANYTHING.

1:53:18.356 --> 1:53:19.444
[MAURIZIO]
OH, DON'T BE SCARED.

1:53:21.577 --> 1:53:23.840
ACTUALLY, BE A LITTLE SCARED.

1:53:23.884 --> 1:53:27.844
THAT... THAT COUCH COSTS MORE
THAN MOST PEOPLE'S APARTMENT
IN MONTE CARLO.

1:53:27.888 --> 1:53:29.846
-OOH.
-[MAURIZIO CHUCKLES]

1:53:29.890 --> 1:53:32.893
-I'LL TRY NOT TO
MAKE A MESS OF IT.
-NO, NO, NO.

1:53:32.936 --> 1:53:34.677
[MAURIZIO] PLEASE, PLEASE.
MAKE A MESS.

1:53:35.852 --> 1:53:37.680
[SOFT BOSSA NOVA MUSIC PLAYING]

1:53:39.073 --> 1:53:40.683
GUCCI WILL PAY FOR IT.

1:53:49.039 --> 1:53:51.694
FOR THE FIRST TIME IN MY LIFE,
I CAN DO WHATEVER I WANT.

1:53:53.914 --> 1:53:55.263
I LIKE THIS SONG.

1:53:57.918 --> 1:53:59.397
TAKE ME BACK TO IPANEMA.

1:54:00.790 --> 1:54:02.531
I'VE NEVER BEEN.
I'VE ALWAYS WANTED TO GO.

1:54:06.404 --> 1:54:07.710
LET'S GO.

1:54:08.232 --> 1:54:09.407
RIGHT NOW.

1:54:10.756 --> 1:54:12.802
[BOSSA NOVA MUSIC
CONTINUES PLAYING]

1:54:15.761 --> 1:54:16.762
[CLEARS THROAT]

1:54:19.548 --> 1:54:22.159
[COUNTING IN SPANISH]

1:54:22.203 --> 1:54:24.596
-OOH.
-[CHUCKLES]

1:54:24.640 --> 1:54:26.468
-CAN YOU DANCE SALSA?
-OF COURSE I CAN.

1:54:26.511 --> 1:54:28.296
[PAOLA CHUCKLES]

1:54:29.950 --> 1:54:31.560
[MAURIZIO] I CAN'T. [CHUCKLES]

1:54:35.172 --> 1:54:36.826
THIS COULD BE A BIG MISTAKE.

1:54:39.046 --> 1:54:40.308
IT'S NOT A MISTAKE.

1:54:41.135 --> 1:54:42.310
IT'S A CHOICE.

1:54:43.746 --> 1:54:45.008
YOU CAN DO WHAT YOU WANT NOW.

1:54:55.018 --> 1:54:56.193
[BOSSA NOVA MUSIC
CONTINUES PLAYING]

1:55:34.318 --> 1:55:36.190
TELL ME WHERE HE IS.

1:55:36.233 --> 1:55:39.410
JUST TELL ME
WHERE HE IS, PINA.

1:55:39.454 --> 1:55:41.064
I COULDN'T SEE.

1:55:41.108 --> 1:55:42.761
YOU'RE FUCKING LYING TO ME!

1:55:43.458 --> 1:55:44.807
WHERE THE FUCK IS HE?

1:55:46.896 --> 1:55:48.376
[PATRIZIA SNIFFLES]

1:55:50.639 --> 1:55:51.814
[SHOUTING]
TELL ME WHERE HE IS?

1:55:56.732 --> 1:55:58.908
["LARGO AL FACTOTUM" PLAYING]

1:56:08.483 --> 1:56:09.223
[CROWD APPLAUDING]

1:56:12.095 --> 1:56:13.618
[MUSIC STOPS]

1:56:13.662 --> 1:56:16.882
[PLAYING CHATTER]

1:56:16.926 --> 1:56:18.884
-WHERE IS HE?
-I'M AFRAID HE COULDN'T COME.

1:56:18.928 --> 1:56:21.017
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
HE COULDN'T COME?

1:56:21.061 --> 1:56:23.106
HE HAD A BUSINESS IN PARIS.

1:56:23.150 --> 1:56:27.676
-HE'S LYING AND SO ARE YOU.
-MAURIZIO IS VERY BUSY,
PATRIZIA.

1:56:27.719 --> 1:56:30.940
HE DIDN'T EVEN HAVE
THE DECENCY TO COME TO
HIS DAUGHTER'S LAST RECITAL.

1:56:30.984 --> 1:56:32.115
WHAT KIND OF A FATHER IS HE?

1:56:33.290 --> 1:56:35.292
THERE WILL BE
A NEW ARRANGEMENT.

1:56:35.336 --> 1:56:37.947
AND WHY DID HE SEND YOU, HUH?

1:56:37.991 --> 1:56:40.036
HEY, DOMENICO,
WHY DID HE SEND YOU?

1:56:40.080 --> 1:56:41.907
WHAT, YOU'RE HIS
LITTLE FUCKING MESSENGER?

1:56:41.951 --> 1:56:43.474
HE DIDN'T HAVE
THE DECENCY TO COME HERE.

1:56:43.518 --> 1:56:45.520
HE'S TOO MUCH OF A COWARD
TO DO IT HIMSELF?

1:56:45.563 --> 1:56:46.738
I HAVE THE PAPERS RIGHT HERE.

1:56:48.088 --> 1:56:49.524
PAPERS?

1:56:49.567 --> 1:56:52.788
AH, PAPERS!
I'M NOT SIGNING ANY PAPERS.

1:56:52.831 --> 1:56:56.661
YOU CAN TELL HIM TO COME HERE
AND TALK TO ME LIKE
A FUCKING NORMAL HUMAN BEING.

1:56:56.705 --> 1:56:59.969
MAURIZIO SAID YOU
AND ALESSANDRA CAN CONTINUE
TO LIVE IN THE PENTHOUSE

1:57:00.013 --> 1:57:02.798
SINCE IT'S NO LONGER
HIS PRIMARY RESIDENCE.

1:57:02.841 --> 1:57:06.367
HE'S HAPPY TO EXTEND PAYMENTS
UNTIL YOU'RE ABLE TO STAND
ON YOUR OWN TWO FEET.

1:57:06.410 --> 1:57:08.804
-WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
-PLEASE.

1:57:08.847 --> 1:57:11.024
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING TO ME?

1:57:11.981 --> 1:57:13.678
HUH?

1:57:13.722 --> 1:57:15.071
-THESE ARE WORDS, DOMENICO.
-SUPPORT FOR ALESSANDRA.

1:57:15.115 --> 1:57:16.942
-I'M NOT TALKING TO YOU.
-SHARED CUSTODY.

1:57:16.986 --> 1:57:18.335
YOU COME TO MY DAUGHTER'S
SCHOOL. WHAT THE FUCK
IS WRONG WITH YOU?

1:57:18.379 --> 1:57:19.249
SHARED CUSTODY. HE WANTS...

1:57:20.903 --> 1:57:22.905
HE WANTS TO MAKE THIS
AS EASY AS POSSIBLE
FOR BOTH OF YOU.

1:57:25.342 --> 1:57:26.561
[TEARFULLY] SHARED CUSTODY?

1:57:27.605 --> 1:57:29.694
ARE WE TALKING ABOUT DIVORCE?

1:57:29.738 --> 1:57:31.305
IS THAT WHAT WE'RE DOING HERE?

1:57:34.438 --> 1:57:35.918
WHERE IS HE RIGHT NOW?

1:57:37.746 --> 1:57:39.269
[SOBBING]
WHERE IS HE RIGHT NOW?

1:57:39.313 --> 1:57:40.488
I'M NOT AT LIBERTY TO SAY.

1:57:41.619 --> 1:57:42.925
LOOK IN MY EYES.

1:57:46.450 --> 1:57:49.758
DO YOU SEE ANYTHING
IN THESE EYES

1:57:49.801 --> 1:57:54.937
THAT WOULD LET YOU THINK
THAT I WOULD EVER LET ANYONE
RUIN MY DAUGHTER'S LIFE?

1:57:56.417 --> 1:57:57.983
COMPROMISE HER.

1:57:59.202 --> 1:58:00.073
DO YOU?

1:58:01.552 --> 1:58:02.858
DO YOU SEE THAT?

1:58:05.643 --> 1:58:08.342
YOU KNOW THAT WON'T HAPPEN.

1:58:10.039 --> 1:58:11.562
I WILL RELAY THE MESSAGE.

1:58:12.433 --> 1:58:14.174
GET THE FUCK OUT OF HERE.

1:58:14.217 --> 1:58:14.957
YEAH.

1:58:24.227 --> 1:58:26.577
FOR YOUR REVIEW, MR. GUCCI.

1:58:26.621 --> 1:58:29.145
WE HOPE YOU'LL FIND
THIS OFFER APPEALING.

1:58:29.189 --> 1:58:31.016
[ALDO] WELL...

1:58:31.060 --> 1:58:35.586
I'D RATHER NOT READ
MY OWN OBITUARY, NO?

1:58:36.848 --> 1:58:39.112
MAESTRO, I CAN ASSURE YOU

1:58:39.155 --> 1:58:41.375
THERE'S NO GREATER ADMIRER
OF GUCCI THAN MYSELF.

1:58:41.418 --> 1:58:42.724
[CHUCKLING]

1:58:42.767 --> 1:58:44.682
OH, GOD.

1:58:44.726 --> 1:58:47.381
TO BE ABLE TO FINALLY SIT DOWN
WITH A MEMBER OF THE DYNASTY.

1:58:48.686 --> 1:58:51.254
IT'S SOMETHING
WE WILL CHERISH FOREVER.

1:58:52.429 --> 1:58:54.083
AND TRULY...

1:58:54.127 --> 1:58:56.825
I UNDERSTAND
HOW DIFFICULT THIS IS.

1:58:56.868 --> 1:58:58.740
PLEASE DON'T PATRONIZE ME.

1:58:58.783 --> 1:59:00.481
PLEASE.

1:59:00.524 --> 1:59:04.398
THOSE WORDS
ARE NOT COMFORTING TO ME.

1:59:04.441 --> 1:59:09.011
THEY MAKE ME FEEL OFFENDED
IN A WAY, I MUST SAY.

1:59:09.707 --> 1:59:11.448
MR. GUCCI,

1:59:11.492 --> 1:59:14.103
I HAVE A PLANE
THAT LEAVES IN ONE HOUR.

1:59:14.147 --> 1:59:15.844
IF THERE IS A PROBLEM
WITH THE OFFER...

1:59:15.887 --> 1:59:17.541
SAID AND OMAR,
THEY'RE AT YOUR DISPOSAL.

1:59:17.585 --> 1:59:19.413
NO, NO, NO.

1:59:19.456 --> 1:59:22.851
[STUTTERING]
WE ARE VERY GRATEFUL
FOR YOUR OFFER...

1:59:22.894 --> 1:59:25.027
EXCEPT NO.

1:59:25.897 --> 1:59:27.203
RIGHT, PAPA?

1:59:27.247 --> 1:59:31.207
THAT SHOE YOU SHOWED ME
BEFORE...

1:59:31.251 --> 1:59:34.689
TAKE A LOOK INSIDE YOUR SHOE
AND SEE AT THE HEEL.

1:59:34.732 --> 1:59:37.213
THERE'S SOMETHING
YOU SHOULD SEE.

1:59:37.257 --> 1:59:41.217
I REMEMBER ORDERING
A PAIR OF THOSE...

1:59:42.000 --> 1:59:43.480
FOR CLARK GABLE.

1:59:44.742 --> 1:59:46.048
1953.

1:59:47.789 --> 1:59:50.183
RIGHT BEFORE
HE DID THE FILM MOGAMBO.

1:59:52.141 --> 1:59:53.925
THIS IS THE RAREST OF SHOES.

1:59:54.926 --> 1:59:57.059
YOU SEE THAT? YOU SEE THAT?

1:59:57.102 --> 1:59:58.408
IT'S A GOLD LEAF.

1:59:59.670 --> 2:00:01.455
YOU KNOW...

2:00:01.498 --> 2:00:03.848
I HAD TO STOP DOING THAT.

2:00:03.892 --> 2:00:05.633
IT GOT TOO EXPENSIVE.

2:00:09.941 --> 2:00:10.899
SO.

2:00:13.162 --> 2:00:14.990
WHERE DID YOU GET THAT SHOE?

2:00:16.078 --> 2:00:17.645
WHERE?

2:00:17.688 --> 2:00:20.778
THERE'S NO WAY YOU BOUGHT
THAT SHOE IN LONDON.

2:00:21.692 --> 2:00:23.085
WHO GAVE IT TO YOU?

2:00:25.305 --> 2:00:26.262
WOULD YOU KNOW?

2:00:28.786 --> 2:00:30.745
MY, HE DOESN'T WANNA ANSWER.

2:00:30.788 --> 2:00:31.963
[PAOLO]
WELL, THAT'S THE LEAST...

2:00:32.007 --> 2:00:33.269
[ALDO] THIS MEETING IS OVER.

2:00:34.314 --> 2:00:36.098
I BROKE UP THE MEETING.

2:00:37.969 --> 2:00:39.580
WHERE IS HE GOING?

2:00:39.623 --> 2:00:41.451
[NEMIR] I'M VERY SORRY.

2:00:41.495 --> 2:00:42.322
I HAD NO CHOICE.

2:00:48.676 --> 2:00:49.677
ALDO.

2:00:51.418 --> 2:00:52.375
[EXCLAIMING]

2:00:53.028 --> 2:00:54.334
DID YOU KNOW THIS?

2:00:56.814 --> 2:00:57.815
NO.

2:00:59.513 --> 2:01:00.949
NO!

2:01:05.258 --> 2:01:06.476
MAURIZIO.

2:01:11.002 --> 2:01:13.483
YOU FUCKING TRAITOR.

2:01:20.925 --> 2:01:21.709
[SIGHS]

2:01:31.806 --> 2:01:32.937
[SOBS]

2:01:54.698 --> 2:01:57.266
THIS IS WHAT YOU WANT?

2:02:13.021 --> 2:02:14.196
[GRUNTS]

2:02:16.807 --> 2:02:18.200
CONGRATULATIONS.

2:02:20.376 --> 2:02:24.902
YOU ARE NOW THE MAJORITY
SHAREHOLDER...

2:02:26.600 --> 2:02:27.644
OF GUCCI.

2:02:29.298 --> 2:02:30.821
YOU MUST FEEL WONDERFUL.

2:02:50.885 --> 2:02:51.799
BOOF.

2:02:56.369 --> 2:02:57.718
[MAN] YOU NEED TO RELAX.

2:02:57.761 --> 2:03:00.024
RELAX. RELAX.

2:03:00.068 --> 2:03:02.897
YOU FLOATING.
YOU FLOATING LIKE
IN THE AIR.

2:03:02.940 --> 2:03:04.377
FLOATING. FLOATING.

2:03:04.420 --> 2:03:07.075
FROM THERE TO THERE.
GO LEFT TO RIGHT.

2:03:07.118 --> 2:03:11.427
[MAURIZIO] MS. WINTOUR,
WALK INTO ANY ONE OF GUCCI'S
144 INTERNATIONAL BOUTIQUES

2:03:11.471 --> 2:03:13.864
AND YOU WILL FIND YOU ARE
WALKING INTO A NEW WORLD.

2:03:13.908 --> 2:03:15.953
A NEW VISION.

2:03:15.997 --> 2:03:20.828
BUT WASN'T THE LURE
OF GUCCI PRECISELY
ITS HISTORICAL APPEAL?

2:03:21.698 --> 2:03:25.136
THE LEGACY IS REMARKABLE.

2:03:25.180 --> 2:03:27.617
[MAURIZIO] WELL, THIS IS TRUE.

2:03:27.661 --> 2:03:30.272
WE ARE PRODUCTS OF OUR PAST
BUT WE DON'T HAVE TO
BE PRISONERS OF IT.

2:03:31.404 --> 2:03:33.449
I DON'T FEAR CHANGE.

2:03:33.493 --> 2:03:34.232
I EMBRACE IT.

2:03:35.799 --> 2:03:40.064
WHERE RALPH LAUREN STORES,
THEY FEEL LIKE MOVIE SETS

2:03:40.108 --> 2:03:42.327
AND VERSACE
IS A ROCK CONCERT,

2:03:42.371 --> 2:03:46.114
GUCCI STORES WILL FEEL
LIKE THE VATICAN OF FASHION.

2:03:46.157 --> 2:03:48.290
["ASHES TO ASHES" PLAYING]

2:03:51.728 --> 2:03:52.729
GRAZIE.

2:04:07.309 --> 2:04:11.444
HOW ARE YOU FUNDING
YOUR VISION?

2:04:11.487 --> 2:04:14.011
-[MAURIZIO] WELL, THAT IS
A VERY GOOD SECRET.
-[CHUCKLES]

2:04:17.406 --> 2:04:18.320
DON'T ASK.

2:04:23.456 --> 2:04:25.414
IT MAY TAKE SOME TIME
TO RECOVER...

2:04:26.459 --> 2:04:29.157
BUT THIS IS A LONG-TERM PLAN.

2:04:29.200 --> 2:04:32.421
SOMETIMES YOU HAVE TO GO DOWN
TO COME BACK UP AGAIN.

2:04:34.075 --> 2:04:37.121
FERRE, ARMANI, AND VERSACE!

2:04:37.165 --> 2:04:39.472
THAT'S WHO I SAID I WANTED
DESIGNING OUR NEW LINE.

2:04:39.515 --> 2:04:41.386
AND THEY WOULD BE HONORED
TO BE WORKING FOR US.

2:04:41.430 --> 2:04:43.476
DE SOLE,
WHERE THE FUCK ARE THEY?

2:04:43.519 --> 2:04:46.957
MAURIZIO, THEY HAVE
THEIR OWN LINES.

2:04:47.001 --> 2:04:48.176
THEY'RE THEIR OWN BOSSES.

2:04:48.219 --> 2:04:50.483
I KNOW THEY HAVE...

2:04:50.526 --> 2:04:52.789
I'VE SPOKEN TO EVERYBODY.
NOBODY WANTS TO...

2:04:52.833 --> 2:04:54.704
THEN YOU HAVEN'T TRIED
HARD ENOUGH.

2:04:56.358 --> 2:04:58.229
THERE IS SOMEONE.

2:04:58.273 --> 2:04:59.796
MAYBE.

2:04:59.840 --> 2:05:00.536
HERE.

2:05:10.024 --> 2:05:11.155
WHO AM I LOOKING AT?

2:05:12.287 --> 2:05:13.810
HE'S FROM TEXAS.

2:05:14.855 --> 2:05:16.073
A MECHANIC?

2:05:17.205 --> 2:05:19.294
MAYBE YOU SHOULD MEET HIM.

2:05:19.337 --> 2:05:22.123
[MAN] I SEE CRANKED UP BLACKS.

2:05:22.166 --> 2:05:24.429
JEWEL-TONE VELVET.

2:05:24.473 --> 2:05:26.431
AND UNCONVENTIONAL
STYLING TOUCHES.

2:05:26.475 --> 2:05:29.086
LOAFERS, SANS SOCKS.

2:05:29.130 --> 2:05:31.349
I SEE POLE DANCERS
FLANKING THE RUNWAYS.

2:05:31.959 --> 2:05:33.090
FEMALE...

2:05:34.309 --> 2:05:35.658
AND MALE, OF COURSE.

2:05:40.271 --> 2:05:45.059
I HAVE A VOCABULARY THAT
WILL ALLOW YOU TO EXPAND.

2:05:45.102 --> 2:05:46.843
THAT'S WHAT THE BRAND REQUIRES.

2:05:46.887 --> 2:05:48.976
THAT'S WHERE WE NEED TO HEAD.

2:05:49.019 --> 2:05:53.197
WITHOUT SACRIFICING
THE FAMILY CHARACTER
OF WHAT THIS BRAND IS.

2:05:53.241 --> 2:05:54.590
THE FAMILY CHARACTER
IS THE BRAND.

2:05:57.027 --> 2:05:59.203
I'M HERE TO EMBELLISH.
I'M HERE TO RESURRECT.

2:06:05.079 --> 2:06:06.123
[CHUCKLES]

2:06:15.698 --> 2:06:17.352
[PATRIZIA] MAURIZIO.

2:06:17.395 --> 2:06:19.441
STOP. PLEASE,
PLEASE, PLEASE.

2:06:19.484 --> 2:06:20.616
I'M BEGGING YOU.
PLEASE STOP.

2:06:22.270 --> 2:06:25.229
OKAY, I--I DON'T WANT
A CONFRONTATION.

2:06:25.273 --> 2:06:26.840
ME NEITHER.

2:06:26.883 --> 2:06:28.319
I TRIED CALLING.

2:06:28.363 --> 2:06:32.628
YES, AND CALLING
AND CALLING AND CALLING.

2:06:32.672 --> 2:06:34.108
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

2:06:34.151 --> 2:06:35.805
I WANT TO TALK.

2:06:35.849 --> 2:06:36.589
[MAURIZIO] OKAY.

2:06:38.678 --> 2:06:40.723
ALESSANDRA MISSES YOU.

2:06:40.767 --> 2:06:42.856
I SAW ALESSANDRA
TWO WEEKS AGO.

2:06:42.899 --> 2:06:44.597
SHE TALKS ABOUT YOU
ALL THE TIME.

2:06:44.640 --> 2:06:47.121
AND I'LL SEE HER VERY SOON.
I'VE BEEN VERY BUSY.

2:06:47.164 --> 2:06:49.123
WILL YOU COME BACK HOME?

2:06:49.166 --> 2:06:51.908
[DISTANT DOG BARKING]

2:06:51.952 --> 2:06:54.476
YOU BOUGHT ALDO AND PAOLO OUT.
YOU DID WHAT I SAID.

2:06:58.088 --> 2:06:59.263
GOOD NIGHT, PATRIZIA.

2:07:00.917 --> 2:07:02.092
[PATRIZIA] COME BACK HOME.

2:07:06.531 --> 2:07:09.404
PATRIZIA, YOU KNOW THAT'S...
THAT'S NOT POSSIBLE.

2:07:10.361 --> 2:07:12.712
NOW, IT IS GETTING VERY LATE.

2:07:13.930 --> 2:07:15.671
GO HOME.

2:07:15.715 --> 2:07:17.542
IF NOT FOR ME,
JUST FOR OUR DAUGHTER.

2:07:17.586 --> 2:07:19.066
[MAURIZIO] NO, NO, NO.
DON'T DO THAT.

2:07:19.109 --> 2:07:20.937
-DON'T...
-DON'T...

2:07:20.981 --> 2:07:22.504
[MAURIZIO]
I'LL TAKE CARE OF HER
AND YOU.

2:07:27.814 --> 2:07:29.859
-[BOTTLE CLINKING]
-[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

2:07:34.255 --> 2:07:35.822
WE MADE SOMETHING
BEAUTIFUL TOGETHER.

2:07:35.865 --> 2:07:36.692
NO, WHAT?

2:07:38.172 --> 2:07:39.303
TAKE IT.

2:07:40.783 --> 2:07:41.915
DO YOU LIKE IT?

2:07:41.958 --> 2:07:43.264
PATRIZIA, WHAT IS THIS?

2:07:43.307 --> 2:07:44.526
DO YOU LIKE IT?

2:07:44.569 --> 2:07:45.875
I MADE IT FOR YOU.

2:07:45.919 --> 2:07:47.529
YOU'RE HUMILIATING YOURSELF.

2:07:52.665 --> 2:07:55.363
WHY ARE YOU TALKING TO ME
THIS WAY?

2:07:55.406 --> 2:07:58.801
BECAUSE YOU CAN'T SEE
WHAT YOU'VE BECOME.

2:07:58.845 --> 2:08:02.370
THIS BOOK... A STORY HAS
A BEGINNING AND AN END.

2:08:02.413 --> 2:08:04.198
AND OURS ENDED
A FEW CHAPTERS AGO.

2:08:05.939 --> 2:08:08.550
SO, WHAT DO YOU WANT
FROM ME NOW?

2:08:10.770 --> 2:08:12.336
I WANT YOU TO MYSELF.

2:08:13.860 --> 2:08:14.991
I LOVE YOU.

2:08:18.342 --> 2:08:19.648
PATRIZIA...

2:08:20.954 --> 2:08:21.911
NO.

2:08:21.955 --> 2:08:23.130
I DON'T LOVE YOU.

2:08:24.609 --> 2:08:26.394
I DON'T HATE YOU...

2:08:26.437 --> 2:08:28.570
BUT I DON'T WANT TO SPEND
THE REST OF MY LIFE WITH YOU.

2:08:29.789 --> 2:08:31.573
NOW, I'M SORRY. I TRULY AM.

2:08:34.315 --> 2:08:36.230
WHAT HAPPENED
TO MY MAURIZIO?

2:08:36.273 --> 2:08:37.666
NOTHING. ABSOLUTELY NOTHING.

2:08:39.015 --> 2:08:40.974
I HAD NO IDEA
I MARRIED A MONSTER.

2:08:42.323 --> 2:08:43.846
YOU DIDN'T.
YOU MARRIED A GUCCI.

2:08:59.644 --> 2:09:01.081
HE'S ALWAYS AWAY ON BUSINESS.

2:09:01.124 --> 2:09:02.778
-HE MOVED, YOU KNOW.
-[GIUSEPPINA] HMM.

2:09:04.258 --> 2:09:05.259
[GIUSEPPINA] MMM-HMM.

2:09:06.347 --> 2:09:08.044
I'VE TOLD YOU SO MANY TIMES.

2:09:08.088 --> 2:09:11.395
HE MOVED INTO THE PENTHOUSE
WITH THAT FUCKING HORSE.

2:09:11.439 --> 2:09:12.657
I'VE SEEN THEM TOGETHER.

2:09:14.485 --> 2:09:16.618
MAYBE YOU SHOULD
STOP FOLLOWING THEM.

2:09:17.706 --> 2:09:19.273
THE THINGS THEY BUY...

2:09:19.316 --> 2:09:23.016
ANTIQUES WORTH BILLIONS,
CARS, PAINTINGS.

2:09:23.059 --> 2:09:24.800
WITH OUR MONEY.

2:09:24.844 --> 2:09:26.628
[GIUSEPPINA]
THAT HE HAS THANKS TO YOU.

2:09:28.630 --> 2:09:30.893
HE'S NOT EVEN A BUSINESSMAN.

2:09:30.937 --> 2:09:32.808
HE CAN'T EVEN
RUN A PARKING METER.

2:09:32.852 --> 2:09:34.810
HOW THE FUCK
IS HE GONNA RUN GUCCI?

2:09:34.854 --> 2:09:36.246
[GIUSEPPINA] YOU'RE RIGHT.

2:09:36.290 --> 2:09:37.857
I KNOW.

2:09:37.900 --> 2:09:39.902
I MADE HIM WHAT HE IS.

2:09:39.946 --> 2:09:42.644
BUT WHEN YOU'RE RIGHT,
YOU'RE RIGHT.

2:09:42.687 --> 2:09:44.646
AND YOU'RE VERY, VERY RIGHT.

2:09:45.690 --> 2:09:47.127
I'M GONNA GO SEE HIM TOMORROW.

2:09:49.869 --> 2:09:53.655
MAYBE YOU SHOULD WAIT
UNTIL WE COME BACK
FROM THE CAYMANS.

2:09:53.698 --> 2:09:55.788
AND THEN WE CAN...

2:09:55.831 --> 2:09:59.269
WE CAN DO
A NICE EVIL EYE ON HIM. HMM?

2:10:01.532 --> 2:10:02.664
ANOTHER SPELL?

2:10:07.538 --> 2:10:08.888
WE'VE RUN OUT OF SPELLS.

2:10:11.716 --> 2:10:13.457
WE NEED SOMETHING STRONGER.

2:10:21.291 --> 2:10:24.904
MAYBE I CAN STILL DO SOMETHING
THAT WILL WORK.

2:10:24.947 --> 2:10:28.733
BUT FOR THAT,
YOU HAVE TO BE POSITIVE.

2:10:39.614 --> 2:10:41.529
I AM BEING
VERY FUCKING POSITIVE.

2:10:43.139 --> 2:10:44.140
[BEEPS]

2:10:45.359 --> 2:10:47.404
[PATRIZIA] YOU ARE
A WASTE OF SKIN

2:10:47.448 --> 2:10:50.494
THAT BELONGS
ON THE FRONT PAGE
OF EVERY NEWSPAPER.

2:10:50.538 --> 2:10:52.322
[ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS]

2:10:52.366 --> 2:10:54.237
I WANT THE WORLD TO KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE REALLY LIKE.

2:10:55.543 --> 2:10:59.329
I WILL NOT GIVE YOU
A MINUTE OF PEACE.

2:10:59.373 --> 2:11:01.592
[ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS]

2:11:01.636 --> 2:11:04.682
YOU TRIED TO CRUSH ME,
BUT YOU COULDN'T.

2:11:05.640 --> 2:11:07.555
[ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS]

2:11:07.598 --> 2:11:11.951
YOU ARE A PAINFUL APPENDAGE
THAT NEEDS TO BE REMOVED.

2:11:11.994 --> 2:11:15.128
THE INFERNO FOR YOU
IS YET TO COME.

2:11:16.433 --> 2:11:17.739
[BIRD CAWING]

2:11:18.435 --> 2:11:19.741
[GREETING IN ITALIAN]

2:11:21.656 --> 2:11:22.526
TWO, RITA.

2:11:22.570 --> 2:11:23.571
WHERE THE FUCK ARE THEY?

2:11:24.615 --> 2:11:26.095
IF I KNEW HOW TO USE A PISTOL,

2:11:26.139 --> 2:11:27.705
I'D FUCKING DO
THIS SHIT MYSELF.

2:11:27.749 --> 2:11:29.098
CALM DOWN. CALM DOWN.

2:11:36.976 --> 2:11:38.281
[GIUSEPPINA]
THEY'LL SHOW UP.

2:11:38.325 --> 2:11:39.369
COME SIT.

2:11:51.555 --> 2:11:52.861
[CAR DOORS CLOSING]

2:11:54.645 --> 2:11:55.690
-THANK YOU.
-ENJOY.

2:12:04.829 --> 2:12:05.613
PINA.

2:12:17.277 --> 2:12:19.366
YEAH.

2:12:19.409 --> 2:12:22.804
IVANO, I TOLD PATRIZIA
THAT I KNOW YOU
SINCE YOU WERE A CHILD, HUH.

2:12:23.892 --> 2:12:25.241
THAT WE TRUST YOU.

2:12:27.678 --> 2:12:29.071
I AM IVANO SAVIONI.

2:12:29.115 --> 2:12:31.204
THIS IS MY ASSOCIATE
BENEDETTO CERAULO.

2:12:39.821 --> 2:12:41.170
WHO DOES WHAT?

2:12:42.955 --> 2:12:44.043
SICILIAN.

2:12:45.740 --> 2:12:48.047
HOW SOON CAN YOU DO IT?

2:12:48.090 --> 2:12:51.006
AS SOON AS
WE KNOW HIS ROUTINE...

2:12:51.050 --> 2:12:53.008
AND HIS SECURITY.

2:12:53.052 --> 2:12:54.923
AND WE ARE SET ON OUR RATE.

2:12:57.360 --> 2:12:59.449
OUR RATE? WHAT RATE?

2:13:02.496 --> 2:13:04.019
-WHAT IS THAT?
-YOU TOLD ME SIX.

2:13:05.064 --> 2:13:07.066
YEAH, YEAH.

2:13:07.109 --> 2:13:09.329
-ARE YOU CRAZY?
-WHY IS HE SAYING EIGHT?

2:13:09.372 --> 2:13:10.983
-I DON'T WHAT HE'S PLAYING.
-WHY THE FUCK
IS HE SAYING EIGHT?

2:13:11.026 --> 2:13:12.636
-NO, I DON'T KNOW.
-WE SAID EIGHT.

2:13:12.680 --> 2:13:14.682
-NO, IT'S SIX.
600 MILLION LIRE.
-WE SAID EIGHT.

2:13:14.725 --> 2:13:16.205
THAT'S IT. WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

2:13:16.249 --> 2:13:17.728
KEEP YOUR FUCKING VOICE DOWN.

2:13:17.772 --> 2:13:19.382
WE SAID EIGHT.

2:13:19.426 --> 2:13:20.470
-I'D CONSIDER IT
IF ONLY IT WAS EIGHT.
-YEAH.

2:13:21.950 --> 2:13:24.039
SOMEBODY ELSE QUOTED ME
FOR FAR LESS.

2:13:25.910 --> 2:13:27.477
SIX IS ALL I'M WILLING TO DO.

2:13:27.521 --> 2:13:29.697
IT WILL HAVE TO BE
A RUSH JOB THEN.

2:13:29.740 --> 2:13:31.960
YEAH.

2:13:32.004 --> 2:13:34.528
-AND YOU HAVE TO PROVIDE
US NOW WITH PHOTOGRAPHS.
-[PATRIZIA] UH-UH-UH.

2:13:34.571 --> 2:13:38.314
SIX IS ALL I WILL PAY.

2:13:38.358 --> 2:13:39.924
WE'LL GIVE YOU HALF NOW...

2:13:41.404 --> 2:13:43.276
HALF LATER WHEN IT'S DONE.

2:13:45.191 --> 2:13:45.887
OKAY.

2:13:46.714 --> 2:13:47.889
OKAY.

2:13:50.370 --> 2:13:52.241
DON'T MISS.

2:13:57.116 --> 2:13:58.073
DEAL WITH HER.

2:14:02.295 --> 2:14:03.948
REALLY.

2:14:03.992 --> 2:14:06.081
YOU DON'T WANNA
MAKE ANY MISTAKES.

2:14:07.126 --> 2:14:07.952
CATCH.

2:14:10.520 --> 2:14:13.480
PAY FOR THE COFFEE
AND DON'T FUCK THIS UP.

2:14:13.523 --> 2:14:15.134
'CAUSE I'LL PUT A SPELL ON YOU.

2:14:19.007 --> 2:14:20.356
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

2:14:24.795 --> 2:14:26.188
READY.

2:14:26.232 --> 2:14:27.755
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

2:14:28.799 --> 2:14:30.192
[AUDIENCE CHEERING]

2:14:30.758 --> 2:14:31.715
WAIT.

2:14:53.433 --> 2:14:54.912
THAT'S AMAZING.

2:14:54.956 --> 2:14:56.958
I THINK HE'S INCREDIBLE.
LOVE HIM.

2:15:08.361 --> 2:15:10.058
ARE YOU SURE
THIS IS A GUCCI SHOW?

2:15:10.102 --> 2:15:11.755
YEAH, YEAH.

2:15:11.799 --> 2:15:15.368
VERY NICE, THIS JACKET,
WE'VE TALKED ABOUT FOR MONTHS.

2:15:17.457 --> 2:15:19.415
IT'S BEAUTIFUL. I LOVE IT.

2:15:19.459 --> 2:15:20.590
YOU'RE IN FOR A SURPRISE.

2:15:22.070 --> 2:15:24.246
[UPBEAT MUSIC CONTINUES]

2:15:30.209 --> 2:15:31.601
[AUDIENCE EXCLAIMING]

2:15:44.397 --> 2:15:45.572
VERY MODERN.

2:15:48.096 --> 2:15:50.403
THREE, TWO, ONE. GO!

2:15:53.536 --> 2:15:54.363
[CROWD CHEERING]

2:16:04.939 --> 2:16:06.027
HE LOOKS GREAT.

2:16:14.383 --> 2:16:15.384
BRAVO!

2:16:16.733 --> 2:16:17.952
BRAVO!

2:16:23.697 --> 2:16:29.268
[TOM FORD] "WHEN TOM FORD
TOOK OVER THE CREATIVE REINS
OF GUCCI IN 1994...

2:16:29.311 --> 2:16:31.922
"THERE WAS LITTLE HOPE FOR
THE MILANESE FASHION HOUSE."

2:16:34.795 --> 2:16:38.277
"IT TOOK A GERMAN DESIGNER
TO STIR UP CHANEL...

2:16:38.320 --> 2:16:42.672
"AND IT IS AN AMERICAN WHO
HAS PUT GUCCI FAR AND AWAY
IN THE FRONT OF FASHION."

2:16:46.241 --> 2:16:49.853
"SOME SAY MR. FORD
WILL GIVE MR. LAGERFELD
A RUN FOR HIS MONEY."

2:16:56.251 --> 2:16:57.905
I HAVE TO CALL MY MOTHER
IN AUSTIN.

2:17:12.920 --> 2:17:15.096
[SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE]

2:17:25.019 --> 2:17:27.369
WHAT AN UNFORGETTABLE NIGHT.

2:17:27.413 --> 2:17:28.283
MAURIZIO.

2:17:29.937 --> 2:17:32.026
AND THE RESPONSE
IS INCREDIBLE.

2:17:32.069 --> 2:17:34.289
I'VE NEVER SEEN
ANYTHING LIKE IT.

2:17:34.333 --> 2:17:37.901
INDEED. IT MARKS
A NEW CHAPTER FOR GUCCI.

2:17:37.945 --> 2:17:41.122
HEY, TRY THE CARPACCIO.
IT MELTS IN YOUR MOUTH.

2:17:41.165 --> 2:17:42.036
OKAY.

2:17:43.951 --> 2:17:45.126
[SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE]

2:17:52.481 --> 2:17:54.309
I THINK WE CAN ALL
BE HONEST WITH EACH OTHER
AROUND THIS TABLE, YEAH?

2:17:54.353 --> 2:17:56.224
WE'RE ALL FRIENDS HERE.

2:17:56.268 --> 2:17:58.139
WE CAN, WE ALL
RESPECT EACH OTHER.

2:17:59.140 --> 2:18:00.141
[MAURIZIO] GRAZIE.

2:18:03.405 --> 2:18:04.841
WE'RE VERY CONCERNED.

2:18:06.930 --> 2:18:09.150
WHAT CONCERNS YOU?

2:18:09.193 --> 2:18:10.934
NUMBERS.

2:18:10.978 --> 2:18:12.371
SPECIFICALLY, GUCCI'S.

2:18:15.112 --> 2:18:17.114
WELL, YOU SAID YOU DIDN'T CARE
ABOUT NUMBERS.

2:18:17.158 --> 2:18:19.813
THAT YOU TRUSTED YOUR INSTINCT.

2:18:19.856 --> 2:18:22.250
YEAH. I CARE ABOUT NUMBERS
WHEN THEY'RE TERRIBLE NUMBERS.

2:18:25.166 --> 2:18:28.300
OUR PROJECTIONS FOR 1996
ARE ABYSMAL.

2:18:29.649 --> 2:18:31.738
BY SLASHING HUNDREDS OF
PROFITABLE ITEMS...

2:18:31.781 --> 2:18:33.522
YOU MEAN
MY UNCLE'S KNICKKNACKS?

2:18:37.613 --> 2:18:41.704
[MAN] LOSSES ARE LIKELY
TO TOTAL $30 MILLION
THIS YEAR ON SALES

2:18:41.748 --> 2:18:43.793
OF $180 MILLION.

2:18:43.837 --> 2:18:46.840
DOWN FROM $210 MILLION IN 1991.

2:18:48.232 --> 2:18:50.191
AND $270 MILLION.

2:18:51.540 --> 2:18:55.065
THERE IS $85 MILLION
IN BANK DEBTS.

2:18:55.109 --> 2:18:59.200
WE MAY EVEN HAVE TROUBLE
PAYING SALARIES FOR
THE NEXT COUPLE OF MONTHS.

2:19:00.201 --> 2:19:03.422
PROFITS REMAIN ELUSIVE.

2:19:03.465 --> 2:19:06.816
AND I'VE ALWAYS SAID
THAT OUR STRATEGIC PLAN
WOULD TAKE FIVE YEARS.

2:19:06.860 --> 2:19:08.601
IT'S NOT ABOUT
IMMEDIATE PROFIT.

2:19:08.644 --> 2:19:10.603
YOU GO DOWN
TO COME BACK UP AGAIN.

2:19:10.646 --> 2:19:12.431
THAT IS HOW YOU GET OUT
OF A STALL.

2:19:12.474 --> 2:19:14.868
BUT THE PERSONAL ITEMS
ARE A CONCERN AS WELL.

2:19:16.565 --> 2:19:20.613
ALL PAID FOR THROUGH
GUCCI'S ACCOUNTS AND
CHARGED AS EXPENSES.

2:19:20.656 --> 2:19:23.050
THE MULTIMILLION-DOLLAR
ANTIQUES IN THE STORES.

2:19:23.093 --> 2:19:24.704
THE PURCHASE
OF COUNTLESS CARS

2:19:24.747 --> 2:19:27.663
INCLUDING A FERRARI F40
AND A LAMBORGHINI COUNTACH.

2:19:27.707 --> 2:19:31.275
$3 MILLION ON A WATCH,
A PATEK PHILIPPE 2523.

2:19:31.319 --> 2:19:33.016
$7 MILLION ON
A LUXURY PENTHOUSE.

2:19:33.060 --> 2:19:34.540
I COULD GO ON AND ON.

2:19:34.583 --> 2:19:37.238
AN 18TH CENTURY PALATIAL VILLA
OUTSIDE FLORENCE

2:19:37.281 --> 2:19:39.240
FOR USE AS A TRAINING CENTER.

2:19:39.283 --> 2:19:41.721
I HAVE JUSTIFICATIONS
FOR ALL OF THESE THINGS

2:19:41.764 --> 2:19:44.680
BUT IT DOESN'T SEEM THAT
YOU'RE IN A PLACE TO HEAR THEM.

2:19:44.724 --> 2:19:48.162
MAURIZIO, PLEASE TRY
AND TAKE THIS IN THE SPIRIT
OF OUR FRIENDSHIP.

2:19:49.772 --> 2:19:51.252
WE'VE BEEN THROUGH
A LOT TOGETHER.

2:19:52.471 --> 2:19:54.647
YOU HAVE MANY QUALITIES.

2:19:54.690 --> 2:19:56.431
BUT WE MUST BE REALISTIC.

2:19:56.475 --> 2:19:59.086
YOU'RE NOT A NATURAL MANAGER.

2:19:59.129 --> 2:20:03.656
YOU CAN'T RUN A BUSINESS
PURELY ON CHARM
AND ECCENTRICITIES.

2:20:03.699 --> 2:20:05.701
NO. YOU NEED TIME AS WELL.

2:20:08.748 --> 2:20:10.706
LAST NIGHT DOES MARK
A NEW CHAPTER FOR GUCCI

2:20:10.750 --> 2:20:12.316
AND I AM THE ONE
THAT BROUGHT IT TO YOU.

2:20:12.360 --> 2:20:15.319
MAURIZIO, I WANT YOU
TO UNDERSTAND

2:20:15.363 --> 2:20:19.149
WHATEVER HAPPENS BETWEEN
BOTH OF OUR COMPANIES,

2:20:19.193 --> 2:20:23.545
I HAVE NEVER STOPPED
RESPECTING YOU OR YOUR VISION.

2:20:25.591 --> 2:20:28.158
BUT I HAVE VISION
FOR MY PEOPLE TOO.

2:20:28.202 --> 2:20:29.899
AND I HAVE A BUSINESS TO RUN.

2:20:37.254 --> 2:20:39.996
WE WANT TO OFFER YOU
$150 MILLION

2:20:40.040 --> 2:20:41.694
FOR YOUR 50% STAKE IN GUCCI.

2:20:41.737 --> 2:20:44.479
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]
YOU WANT TO BUY ME OUT.

2:20:44.523 --> 2:20:46.089
[DOMENICO]
WE WANT TO SAVE THE BUSINESS.

2:20:47.221 --> 2:20:49.179
AND WHO WOULD BE
APPOINTED CEO?

2:20:56.926 --> 2:20:58.101
[CHUCKLES]

2:21:00.930 --> 2:21:02.323
SHE WAS RIGHT ABOUT YOU.

2:21:07.023 --> 2:21:09.504
$150 MILLION.

2:21:09.548 --> 2:21:10.984
YOU'LL BE A RICH MAN.

2:21:11.027 --> 2:21:12.507
IF YOU REALLY THINK
IT'S ABOUT MONEY,

2:21:12.551 --> 2:21:15.205
THEN YOU KNOW LESS ABOUT GUCCI
THAN I THOUGHT.

2:21:17.251 --> 2:21:18.557
[SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE]

2:21:32.179 --> 2:21:33.354
[SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE]

2:21:38.751 --> 2:21:40.056
-EXCUSE ME.
-YES.

2:21:40.100 --> 2:21:42.450
THIS MEAT.
WHERE IS IT COMING FROM?

2:21:42.494 --> 2:21:44.713
THIS IS THE FINEST BEEF
IN TUSCANY.

2:21:44.757 --> 2:21:46.541
IT COMES FROM
THE VAL DI CHIANA.

2:21:46.585 --> 2:21:48.369
THE COWS
ARE TREATED LIKE ROYALTY.

2:21:57.857 --> 2:21:58.727
[SIGHS]

2:21:59.598 --> 2:22:00.860
[DOOR SLAMS SHUT]

2:22:02.818 --> 2:22:06.561
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2:22:17.224 --> 2:22:19.531
[HORN BLARING INCESSANTLY]

2:22:22.403 --> 2:22:25.449
[ALARM BEEPING]

2:25:20.407 --> 2:25:22.061
THAT'S HIM.

2:25:22.104 --> 2:25:23.366
-GOOD MORNING!
-[MAURIZIO GREETING
IN ITALIAN]

2:25:36.815 --> 2:25:38.033
SIGNORGUCCI?

2:25:41.907 --> 2:25:44.605
-[GUNSHOT]
-[GRUNTS]

2:25:46.215 --> 2:25:47.739
-[GUNSHOT]
-[GROANING]

2:25:57.139 --> 2:25:58.227
WHAT'S GOING ON?

2:25:59.054 --> 2:26:00.055
[MAN GROANS]

2:26:45.927 --> 2:26:48.582
[SOFT INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC
PLAYING]

2:27:28.100 --> 2:27:29.492
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

2:27:32.582 --> 2:27:34.628
[HORNS HONKING]

2:27:36.630 --> 2:27:38.632
[REPORTERS CLAMORING]

2:28:14.146 --> 2:28:15.190
[SIGHS]

2:28:17.845 --> 2:28:18.759
PATRIZIA.

2:28:26.985 --> 2:28:28.160
[PATRIZIA CRYING]

2:28:29.030 --> 2:28:29.770
I KNOW.

2:28:39.823 --> 2:28:42.348
PLEASE SEE SIGNORINAFRANCHI
OUT OF MY HOUSE.

2:29:28.785 --> 2:29:31.527
["BABY CAN I HOLD YOU" PLAYING]

2:29:44.976 --> 2:29:46.325
[MALE JUDGE] SIGNORAREGGIANI.

2:29:50.546 --> 2:29:51.852
SIGNORAREGGIANI.

2:29:54.550 --> 2:29:55.638
[GAVEL BANGING]

2:29:55.682 --> 2:29:56.988
SIGNORAREGGIANI.

2:29:58.554 --> 2:29:59.729
[GAVEL POUNDING]

2:30:05.300 --> 2:30:08.521
YOU CAN CALL ME SIGNORAGUCCI.

